·       Strong analytical skills

·       Programming experience in python or similar is preferable

·       Independent and passionate about the future of ship technology 

 

**2.Market and strategy (2 positions)**

We are looking for motivated strategy interns to support us on our journey to shape the company into an international success story. You will take an active part in setting the strategic direction for the company by connecting the dots between market insight and our growth ambitions. You will work with researching and analyzing market trends, market offerings, competitive landscape, pricing and business models.

 

Your responsibilities can include:

·       Conduct market research of target markets and geographies, consolidate and analyze data into actionable information

·       Map commercial opportunities in target markets

·       Due diligence work on suppliers, partners, and yards

·       Develop business cases for operational initiatives

 

Recommended profile and experience:

·       3rd or 4th year students within business administration, industrial economics, marine technology or similar

·       Strong analytical skills

·       Experience with qualitative and quantitative analysis either from school or work

·       Interest for strategy and business development

·       Collaborative attitude

 

**3.Software developer (2 positions)**

A part of our strategy is to deliver digital systems to increase the efficiency, reliability and safety of our vessels. We have big ambitions, and are seeking highly skilled, motivated and self-driven students to contribute in creating revolutionary vessels. Do you want to join us writing software that will cut emissions?

 

Your responsibilities can include design and implementation of:

·       Over-the-air software upgrade system

·       Ride control system

·       Onboard user interface

·       Other various software components on the vessel and in our cloud environment

·       Web dashboard

·       Remote monitoring system

·       Machine learning algorithms enabling more fuel-efficient control

 

Recommended profile and experience:

·       3rd and 4th year students within cybernetics, data science, informatics, industrial design

·       Motivated and self-driven with interest for software development

·       Experience with one or more of: Linux, network/VPN, AWS, C++, CoDeSys, Front-end, Back-end, embedded systems, PLC Programming

 

**What we offer:**

1.   Opportunities in a fast-growing maritime technology company

2.   Possibility to contribute to green ship technology for the future

3.   Oslo-based summer job with possibility for part time job

4.   Competitive salary

5.   Possibility for project-work and Master’s Thesis for 4th year students 

 

**Practical information:**

 

**Start date:** Spring / summer 2021, to be discussed

**Duration:** Full time / part time

**Location:** Oslo / remote

**Contact person:** 

Silje Haugland

Silje.haugland@sesxmarinetechnologies.com

+47 971 33 311

 

Please include your CV, cover letter and transcripts in the application. Also, make sure to mention which internship position you are most interested in applying for in your cover letter.', '2021-02-01 16:48:42+00', '2021-03-01 22:59:59+00', false, '2021-03-01 22:59:59+00', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/2409015200/?refId=Ob0V4qiZQVWujsioD3zE6g%3D%3D', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (33, NOW(), 11, 'Summer job SINTEF ICT ', '"Software development, integration and experimentation', 'As part of several projects, SINTEF ICT has developed a prototype of an emergency management system to be used when trialing new technologies and concepts together with alarm centers and municipalities. The prototype consist of a server-side application responsible for receiving and managing alarms (such as an elderly fall), a fall detection application and a care-giver mobile application. The work in this summer job revolves around this prototype and it includes: the further development of the server-side application, the development of the care-giver mobile application and the integration of all the parts. On top of that, it includes the experimentation of a few technologies in the context of the prototype which includes the new different health toolkits (such as Google Fit and Apple Health) and the usage of trust enabling technologies developed in the EU Project OPTET. 

