INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (77, NOW(), 54, 'Rails / React Native Internship', 'Introduction Ebby is an online marketplace that connects you with a driver, so that you can order food from the biggest fast food chains in the city straight to your door. Wouldn''t it be cool if McDonald''s could do home deliveries? It''s about time. W', 'We are looking for a Ruby on Rails or React Native developer responsible for managing the interchange of data between the server and the users. Your primary focus will be development of server-side logic,, and ensuring high performance and responsiveness to requests from the front-end. We’re also working on giving our drivers a native mobile app using React Native.
 
### Responsibilities

  - Design, build, and maintain efficient, reusable, and reliable Ruby code
  - Integration of user-facing elements developed by front-end developers with server side logic
  - Identify bottlenecks and bugs, and devise solutions to these problems
  - Help maintain code quality, organization and automation.
  - If you’re a React Native developer, you’ll be working with us on establishing our driver app.
 
### Skills

  - Experience with Ruby on Rails
  - Good understanding of the syntax of Ruby and its nuances
  - Solid understanding of object-oriented programming
  - Basic understanding of front-end technologies, such as JavaScript, HTML5 and CSS3
  - Familiarity with concepts of MVC, Mocking, ORM, and RESTful
  - A knack for writing clean, readable Ruby code
  - Understanding of fundamental design principles behind a scalable application
- Able to implement automated testing platforms and unit tests
  - Proficient understanding of code versioning tools e.g. Git.
- Familiarity with continuous integration
 
### Internship period

The internship period will last from July till end of August (2 months), and is paid. You’ll be working in Oslo, Norway at our modern office located at Simula Research Laboratory, on IT Fornebu. You’ll be working with our main developer, and tasked with assignments that suit your current level of expertise - allowing you to get help and feel comfortable. 

### How to apply

Send a short summary to sebastian@ebby.no telling us about yourself and what you enjoy about coding. Standard false negatives are highly discouraged. Please make it genuine.
 
### What we offer you
Besides 200,- per hour during the part time internship, we offer you the opportunity to be a part of our core team. This is a startup, and you will be working with 3 of the most hard working guys in Oslo, determined to make it whatever it takes. You will be joining us in the middle of our launch, and will experience something you will learn a lot from.


 
*Søknadsfrist: 15. April 2016*

*Kontaktinfo: Sebastian Jennings Almnes*

*Tlf: 468 29 291*

*Email: sebastian@ebby.no*

*Alle snakker norsk!*', '2016-04-07 00:00:00+00', '2016-04-15 00:00:00+00', false, NULL, '', '', 'OTHER', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (76, NOW(), 49, 'Nordea søker faste ansatte til Graduate program', 'Nordea tilbyr fra høsten to spennende grauateprogram for deg med master, søk nå!', '### Stilling 1: Graduate to Group Functions IT - Data Engineer 


Nordea is a bank with a lot of data. Data is critical to our business and our customers. We harness the power of data
to understand the needs of our customers, provide our customers with a true digital experience through all our
contact points with them and tailor our products to best meet their needs. Data is also our primary ammunition in the
fight against wrong doing and bad behaviour as it powers our defensive capability in Risk, Fraud and Financial Crime.
We are looking for people who understand the complexities of data and the techniques that are applied to raw
information to gain insight from data.
The day to day tasks can take many forms from working out a single view of a Customer (Entity Resolution) to plotting
a visualisation that shows the money flow between customers in the global supply chain (graph analytics).
Working in the Group Functions IT team will give you exposure to all the core data in Nordea and the challenges it
brings. You will be working on the production of the largest data platform in the bank that produces reporting and
analytics to regulators, customers and internal management.


## Qualifications 

- A Master’s degree
- A maximum of two years’ post-academic work experience
-  Excellent English language skills
- Applied statistical knowledge
- High level programming: SQL, R, Python
- Data Visualisation experience: D3, Matlab
- Understanding of Corporate Finance / Global Markets


### Stilling 2: Graduate to Group Functions IT - Data Science

Nordea is a bank with a lot of data. Data is critical to our business and our customers. We harness the power of data
to understand the needs of our customers, provide our customers with a true digital experience through all our
contact points with them and tailor our products to best meet their needs. Data is also our primary ammunition in the
fight against wrong doing and bad behaviour as it powers our defensive capability in Risk, Fraud and Financial Crime.
We are looking for people who understand the complexities of taking data in a raw format, through data processing
layers and providing a finished consumable product through a Rest API or SQL layer.
The day to day tasks can take many forms from getting a 30 year old mainframe to talk nicely to its internet
grandchildren to working on a continual release process that allow multiple version of our code base to operate in
parallel.

### Qualifications 

- A Master’s degree
- A maximum of two years’ post-academic work experience
- Excellent English language skills
- Deep programming skills in Java, C++, C#, Javascript
- Knowledge of distributed systems, CAP Theorem
- Continuous integration and distributed source control
- Understanding of Corporate Finance / Global Markets 

### Extra: 

You need to pass an ability test that assesses numerical, verbal and inductive capabilities. In addition,
we expect you to have personal ambition and to be a team player. You are confident, driven and possess the mindset
to constantly improve your competencies and to develop.

Both positions also requires a permanent work permit in Denmark.


### Søknad må inkludere: 
Applications are to be submitted in English, including a cover letter, (other documents, if applicable,) and a CV.

Søknadsfrist : 
28.03.16 

Søknad og evt spørsmål sendes på mail til Alasdair.anderson@nordea.com, telefon : +45 21310081', '2016-03-15 00:00:00+00', '2016-03-29 00:00:00+00', false, NULL, '', '', 'OTHER', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (384, NOW(), 7, 'Summer Internship 2020 – Bli med å skape det nye Norge!', 'Vil du teste ut livet som konsulent hos oss? Seks uker av sommeren 2020 har du mulighet til å komme tett på bedriftskulturen vår og rett og slett, få en uforglemmelig sommer!', '# Job Description

