#### Job duties typically include 
- Software development in C++ and/or Python  
- Analyzing requirements and development of functional and non-functional specifications for the product 
- User interface design and implementation  
- Cross platform development for Linux/Windows
- Team Work. Work with other staff to efficiently and effectively coordinate work activities (Scrum process)  

#### Candidates should have  
- Completed BSc and preferably first half of a Master degree in computer science, or similar coupled with relevant experience from software development.
- A strong interest in developing high quality, user friendly software

Whether you want to help solve practical issues or spend the summer diving into complex problems, get in touch and we’ll see what happens. We are large enough to provide you with broad professional support, yet small enough for your performance to make a difference. Roxar has a challenging environment where people can learn, experiment and grow.  

The working language at Roxar is English.  

Show us your code - If you have code to show on GitHub, Bitbucket or the like, we''d love to see it! Feel free to provide a link along with your application and CV.  

#### Job details
**Place:** Lysaker, Oslo or Stavanger   
**Start date:** June 2018  
