**Examples of projects that have been offered:**

-   Real time multi head pose detection.
-   Improving the microphone beam selector using deep learning.
-   Office room analytics application based on live and historical sensor data from our devices.
-   Noise reduction with deep learning.
-   Synchronous camera focusing for immersive systems.
-   Showing personal calendars in meeting rooms based on face recognition.

**Our dream candidate:**

-   You are studying towards a master’s/bachelor´s degree in a related subject
-   You have an attractive academic record to show to
-   You have a genuine interest in technology and a willingness to learn
-   You have some practical engineering experience (e.g. you are a programmer or have hands on skills with testing, signal processing, network protocols or cloud technology).
-   You are a 3rd or 4th year student, but we very much encourage 1st or 2nd year students to apply as well.
-   You are able to live and work in Norway

**Your opportunities - why Cisco:**

-   You will join a world-class team with over 60% market share for our collaboration products
-   Our interns will typically join a real project team and do a useful task for Cisco while working here.
-   We can promise that we will provide challenging and interesting tasks that are relevant to your education and creativity.
-   We can offer you a fun summer with a competitive salary, - and of course - free ice cream during warm summer days.

**Work Location:** Lysaker, just outside of Oslo

**Duration:** Mid-June – Mid-August 2021 (we can be flexible on this)

**First Application Deadline:** 31st of October 2020 - we review applications on an ongoing basis

**Upon applying please upload your cover letter, CV and university grade transcript. For any questions you can reach us on  [jobs-lysaker@cisco.com](mailto:jobs-lysaker@cisco.com)**', '2020-10-07 13:15:50+00', '2020-10-31 22:59:59+00', false, '2020-10-31 22:59:59+00', 'https://jobs.cisco.com/jobs/IsAJob?projectId=1296228&source=Other+Job+Posting&tags=onlinentnu', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (437, NOW(), 103, 'Passionate Early Career Software Developer', 'We’re Equinor, an international energy company with a proud history. Formerly Statoil, we are 20,000 committed colleagues developing oil, gas, wind and solar energy in more than 30 countries worldwide.', 'We’re the largest operator in Norway, one of the world’s largest offshore operators, and a growing force in renewables. Driven by our Nordic urge to explore beyond the horizon, and our dedication to safety, equality and sustainability, we’re building a global business on our values and the energy needs of the future.  
  
Advanced information technology, data science and software development are key enablers to realize our ambitions. We have a strong 300+ inhouse software community collaborating across development sites in Stavanger (Forus), Bergen (Sandsli), and Trondheim (Rotvoll). Things we are working on include words like: Python, Azure, timeseries, machine learning, C++, GitHub, GraphQL, open source, k8s, Rust, optimization, React Native, microservices, security, Linux, GPU, robotics, SAP, Java, Jupyter, and supercomputing.  

We have built a culture around software craftsmanship, open source and knowledge sharing. We embrace free and open data and software license models. Most new projects are being developed openly on GitHub ([https://github.com/equinor](https://github.com/equinor)). We have a big annual inhouse developer conference, software craftsmanship days, frequent training courses and we try to be an active partner and contributor to the Norwegian software community. Read more at [loop.equinor.com](loop.equinor.com)  
  
This ad is part of an ongoing recruitment. Applications will be handled on a continuous basis.  
  

#### Job Description

We are looking for people that are early in their career and that have a passion for software development. If you have a master''s degree or PhD in informatics, computer science or computer engineering with 0-3 years of relevant experience, you are the one we are looking for. We need your help to solve the challenges the largest energy company in Norway face in the age of digitalization.  
At Equinor you will join cross functional teams of professionals working together with customers to produce solutions that add value to the business. It is a goal that every member contributes to the whole development cycle. This include taking part in the dialogue with customers, implementation, code reviews, design and support. We aim for teams that are long lived, autonomous and self-organizing and capable of finding their own way to collaborate and achieve their goals. We value software craftsmanship and expect everyone to share knowledge, build competence and contribute to building a stronger team.  
  

#### Qualifications

• Master''s degree or PhD in informatics, computer science or computer engineering  
• 0-3 years of relevant experience  
• We frequently use Python, C#, C/C++, Java and Javascript variants so experience with these are a plus  
• Good knowledge with algorithms, mathematics or physics  
• Experience with statistics, visualization [and|or] machine learning is beneficial  
• Experience with open source is a plus  
  
Candidates with bachelor’s degree and 2-3 years of solid software development experience can be considered.  
  

#### Personal Qualities

While strong technical skills are important, we are also looking for communication and collaboration skills, professionalism, innovative mindsets, and people that are eager to learn and develop. We are particularly looking for people that can contribute to our vibrant and fast growing inhouse professional software community. We encourage diversity in terms of abilities, gender, age and culture.  
  
Ability to live by our safety and security expectations.  
  

#### We Offer

Not just a job: a career. We encourage you to take advantage of the many opportunities our global company offers, and empower you to build your career across multiple disciplines and geographies, exchange ideas and learn from others.  
  
Rewards. We offer a range of reward programmes within one Equinor framework adapted to the local market. This includes competitive salary, variable pay schemes and a share savings plan.  
  
Wellness and work-life balance. Our employees’ health and well-being is a priority and we encourage our people to make use of our flexible work arrangements to help balance their work and home lives efficiently.  
  
An inclusive culture. Embracing an inclusive culture is a fundamental part of our values, and leveraging our diverse perspectives and experiences help us deliver together.  
  
If you are eager to innovate or learn new programming languages and new technologies we provide you with the possibility to use up to 20% of your time on innovation and competence building.  
  

#### General Information

Make sure that we are able to give your application consideration: Please attach copies of your diplomas, certificates and grades in English or Norwegian (or another Scandinavian language). Applications submitted without such attachments will unfortunately not be evaluated. If you are in the process of completing a degree, please upload an official temporary transcript or other document describing subjects and grades completed to this point.  
  
Our values are to be courageous, open, collaborative and caring. We believe in these qualities, which are essential for building an even stronger Equinor. If you can identify with them, you could be the one to strengthen our team.  
  
Candidates are expected to openly offer all relevant information about themselves during the recruitment process.  
  
All hires will be screened against relevant sanctions lists to ensure compliance with sanctions law and increase security.  
  
If you have questions about the position or the process please send an email to gm_equinoremea@equinor.com.  
  
Please be aware that no applications or attachments to applications will be accepted via email.  
  
