INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (347, NOW(), 103, 'Graduate 2020 - Information Technology And Digitalisation', 'Do you want to contribute to shaping the future of energy? Join our corporate graduate programme!  We are always looking to attract the best and most qualified talents. We offer an introduction to Equinor and the energy industry and focus on accelera', 'We’re Equinor, an international energy company with a proud history. Formerly Statoil, we are 20,000 committed colleagues developing oil, gas, wind and solar energy in more than 30 countries worldwide. We’re the largest operator in Norway, one of the world’s largest offshore operators, and a growing force in renewables. Driven by our Nordic urge to explore beyond the horizon, and our dedication to safety, equality and sustainability, we’re building a global business on our values and the energy needs of the future.

The world will need a lot more energy and lower emissions in the years to come, and we’re determined to be part of the solution. It’s not an easy job, but we believe that with the right people, passion and curiosity, it is possible.  
  
  

Our Corporate Graduate Programme is aimed at applicants with both technical and non-technical backgrounds who have recently graduated or will be able to graduate by the end of 2020 with a master’s or PhD degree. Graduates in Equinor will have a steep learning curve and are expected to develop an overall understanding of our activities and business challenges.  
  
Our Corporate graduate programme will:  
• Start your transition from student to professional, with opportunities to contribute in some of our company’s most exciting tasks.  
• Offer you permanent employment from your first day, and enrollment in the programme for two years.  
• Give you challenging and meaningful tasks and an opportunity to work with your own development goals that correspond with Equinor’s business needs.  
• Let you participate in structured learning and networking, engage in rotational assignments and have a mentor throughout the programme.  
  
Our graduates can work within different disciplines throughout the company. You can read more about the various disciplines  
[here](https://www.equinor.com/en/careers/our-graduate-disciplines.html).  
  
  

#### Job Description

Equinor’s ambition is to be a leader within its core operations. Digital technologies will support this through improved safety, increased value creation, reduced carbon footprint and enabling new business models. Equinor is a leader in utilizing cutting edge digital technologies and has vast quantities of data, but the full potential of this data is yet to be unlocked using advanced technology such as cloud computing, microservice architectures, machine learning, artificial intelligence etc.  
  
The IT-unit (~750 employees) works closely with the business, supporting and delivering business driven solutions throughout Equinor. The Digital Center of Excellence (~40 employees) is responsible for shaping Equinor''s digital ambition, incubate new cross cutting digital initiatives and support digital projects.  
  
Fields within discipline:  
• Information Technology  
• Software development  
• Data analytics, data science and Artificial Intelligence (AI)  
• IT security and risk management  
• Enterprise data management  
• Automation, robotics and remote control  
  
  

#### Qualifications

• Master’s degree or PhD with good academic record withn STEM or Humanities  
• No more than two years of relevant fulltime work experience  
• Fluent in English and preferably a second working language  
• International work and/or study experience preferred  
• Extracurricular activities and/or voluntary work is an advantage  
  
  

#### Personal Qualities

• Ability to live by our safety and security expectations  
• High ethical standards  
• Good communication skills  
• Global mindset  
• Team player with the ability to work and deliver results in a diverse environment  
• Have a positive attitude to take on new challenges and adapt to dynamic environments  
  
  

#### We Offer

Not just a graduate program. A global career kick start. We encourage you to take advantage of the many opportunities our global company offers, and empower you to build your career across multiple disciplines and geographies, exchange ideas and learn from others.  
  
Rewards. We offer a range of reward programmes within one Equinor framework adapted to the local market. This includes competitive salary, variable pay schemes and a share savings plan.  
  
Wellness and work-life balance. Our employees’ health and well-being is a priority and we encourage our people to make use of our flexible work arrangements to help balance their work and home lives efficiently.  
  
An inclusive culture. Embracing an inclusive culture is a fundamental part of our values, and leveraging our diverse perspectives and experiences help us deliver together.  
  
  

#### General Information

Please make sure that when applying, you attach the following:  
• CV/ resume in English  
• Transcripts of records (or other documents describing subjects and grades) obtained to this point during your studies in English or Scandinavian language. If you are in the process of completing a degree, please upload an official temporary transcript.  
Applications submitted without these attachments will unfortunately not be evaluated.  
  
Our values are to be open, collaborative, courageous and caring. We believe in these qualities, which are essential for building an even stronger Equinor. If you can identify with them, you could be the one to strengthen our team.  
  
Our safety expectations: Safety is integrated in everything we do and are applicable to all - “I am safety” Accountable, visible and engaged.  
  
Candidates are expected to openly offer all relevant information about themselves during the recruitment process.  
All permanent and temporary hires will be screened against relevant sanctions lists to ensure compliance with sanctions law and increase security.  

To apply [click here](https://careers.peopleclick.eu.com/careerscp/client_statoil/external/en-us/jobDetails.do?functionName=getJobDetail&jobPostId=20890&localeCode=en-us)
  
For technical issues and other queries please contact us at  [GraduateRecruitment@equinor.com](mailto:%20GraduateRecruitment@equinor.com)', '2019-08-15 12:57:41+00', '2019-09-22 21:59:59+00', false, '2019-09-22 21:59:59+00', '', '', 'OTHER', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (393, NOW(), 41, 'Lønnet sommerjobb for teknologiinteresserte studenter', 'Vi gir deg 6 uker på å lage en samfunnsnyttig løsning for fremtiden. Tar du utfordringen?', '#### Vi gir deg 6 uker på å lage en samfunnsnyttig løsning for fremtiden. Tar du utfordringen?
Gjennom sommerjobben hos Geodata får du mulighet til å teste hvordan det er å jobbe som konsulent. Sommerjobben er designet for å gi deg en smakebit på arbeidslivet med kreative og kompetansebyggende rammer.

#### Sommerjobben
I løpet av seks uker vil du få muligheten til å jobbe med en spennende prosjektoppgave sammen med studenter fra ulike studieretninger. 

Den første uken vil dere bli satt inn i hvordan Geodata jobber med å lage løsninger for kundene sine. Dere vil lære mer om hvordan vi skaper kreative prosesser gjennom brainstorming og teamdynamikk. I tillegg vil dere få innføring i vår programvare og de programmeringsverktøyene som kreves for å løse prosjektoppgaven. Resten av sommerjobben vil gå med til å arbeide med løsningen dere har valg og avsluttes med en presentasjon av resultatet. Dere vil selv ha stor påvirkning på hvilke nye teknologietrender dere ønsker å ta i bruk. De to siste årene har valget falt på sensordata, Big Data og maskinlæring.
 
#### Hvem er du?

Går du en relevant studieretning og har et ønske om å jobbe med brukeropplevelse, IT, programmering og/eller GIS-teknologi er dette sommerjobben for deg.

Vi ser etter studenter med ulik studiebakgrunn, som sammen kan danne et spennende team. For å løse prosjektoppgaven trenger teamet kunnskap om:  

- GIS og Esri sin programvare  
- utvikling og programmering
- datakommunikasjon, interaksjonsdesign og brukeropplevelse

I tillegg til å ha kompetanse innenfor et eller flere av fagområdene over:

- behersker du norsk, dansk eller svensk skriftlig og muntlig  
- er du i et pågående studium
- er du kreativ og løsningsorientert
- har du IT-teknisk interesse

#### Hvorfor skal du søke?
  
- Du trenger penger, men samtidig vil du også ha litt ferie i sommer 
- Du trenger relevant arbeidserfaring - gjerne i et IT-selskap som er markedsledende i sitt fagfelt
- Du ønsker å benytte kunnskapen din til å lage noe innovativt og samfunnsnyttig
- Du kunne tenkte deg å være i Oslo i sommer 
- Du ønsker kompetanseheving gjennom praktisk prosjektarbeid
- Du anser det som verdifullt å komme nærmere en bedrift med et ettertraktet traineeprogram 
- Du vil helst ha en sommerjobb hvor det er et spennende fagmiljø med dyktige, hyggelige og sporty ansatte

