INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (336, NOW(), 136, 'Leading FinTech company is looking for students with Machine Learning skills!', 'For this position we are looking for tech-savvy students with machine learning expertise to join us for internships this summer and potentially part time and thesis collaboration during the fall.', '**Job description**

For this position we are looking for tech-savvy students with machine learning expertise to join us for internships this summer and potentially part time and thesis collaboration during the fall. As part of the backend team you will contribute in the development of highly innovative products by using ML/quantitative techniques related to natural language processing and financial time series, both for internal use and as products deployed towards our customers.

**Topics we will explore includes:**

- Real-time highly scalable recommender systems
- Robo-journalism by deep neural networks

**The candidate we are looking for**
- Masters/Phd student in computer science, data science, statistics or other related field
- You are required to have hands-on experience with machine learning models through school projects or internships. Textual sources and time-series data will be our main focus.
- Proficient in Python and experience with databases (SQL and/or NoSQL)
- Experience with at least a couple of the most common ml/ds libraries, such as Scikit, Tensorflow, Pytorch, Numpy or Pandas.
- Creative and entrepreneurial mindset
- Knowledge of other programming languages such as C++, C#, JavaScript is a plus
- Knowledge of distributed architecture and cloud platforms (Microsoft Azure) is a plus 
- Good command of English, both written and oral
- Interest in financial markets

**Why Infront?**

Infront offers an exciting and challenging job within the financial technology sector. You will be a part of an active social environment with friendly, supportive and highly skilled colleagues. Being part of a company based on technological innovation will give you opportunities for personal growth and fulfilling career possibilities in a fast-paced environment. At the same time, we have an informal and relaxed culture based on mutual trust, respect and cooperation. Grab this opportunity to become a part of the Infront culture, where contributions are recognized and achievements are celebrated.

**How to apply**

If you think you’re the right candidate, please send us a short application with CV, overview over relevant courses taken and link to projects at GitHub etc, by using the apply for position functionality located next to our ad on FINN:  
[https://www.finn.no/job/parttime/ad.html?finnkode=129703740](https://www.finn.no/job/parttime/ad.html?finnkode=129703740)

  
Application deadline is May 5th, but we encourage you to apply as soon as possible as we will start to review candidates earlier.

Alongside the paid positions, we are also interested in thesis collaboration with ambitious students eager to apply machine learning to textual data in the context of news and finance. Get in touch if this sounds like you.  

We look forward to hear from you.', '2019-04-08 17:00:00+00', '2019-05-05 21:59:59+00', false, '2019-05-05 21:59:59+00', '', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

