INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (443, NOW(), 98, 'Summer Project 2020', 'Are you interested in spending your summer making a carbon free future possible, and would you enjoy designing new opportunities in the energy transition?', '*Are you interested in spending your summer making a carbon free future possible, and would you enjoy designing new opportunities in the energy transition?*


We are proud to present our annual summer project 2020, which  provides the opportunity to come up with new ideas and business models  that will contribute to a carbon free future. As a summer intern you  will be working in a diverse and multidisciplinary team of 6-8 students. You can expect responsibility from day one, with close follow up from  designated and motivated mentors. Our summer students are highly  qualified employees and you will actively contribute to the further  development and growth of Statkraft. We encourage students with a  curious and creative mind to apply!

This summer we invite students to develop new ideas for our EV charging business. The industry is now  investing massively and building a framework for sustainable transport  and to reduce emissions. Change in consumer behaviour, regulations and  sustainability-oriented technologies are driving this change. Statkraft, who has made clean energy possible for over a century, is now taking a  powerful position in decarbonising transport with renewable energy by  providing electric vehicle charging to a growing market.

We are  looking for students who wish to explore and develop new adjacent  business ideas within the EV charging space, beyond the current business models around supply, installation and operation of fast- and  slow-charging equipment. The project contributes to create value and a  pole position in the coupling of the energy and mobility sectors.  

You will present the outcome of the project to our Corporate Management and the broader organisation by the end of the period. The project will be  based in Oslo and last from mid-June – mid-August.

*Want to know more about Statkraft''s involvement in EV charging? Check out this* **[article](https://explained.statkraft.com/articles/2019/electrification-statkraft-expands-its-focus-on-electric-car-charging/).**

**Who are we looking for?**

We are looking for a diverse team with various backgrounds ranging from  computer science and IT, mathematics, physics, industrial-, electrical-, mechanical engineering, business/strategy, economics, natural sciences, renewable energy studies, or other area of relevance. Some key skills  we are looking for are:

- Ability to think and reason commercially
- Strong analytical skills and result oriented
- Entrepreneurial mindset
- Team player with good communicative skills
- Cultural awareness
- Great passion for business and the renewable industry
- Preferably 3-4 years of higher education with solid academic results
- Fluent in English

**Statkraft offers:**

- Professional and personal development in a company experiencing strong growth
- A positive working environment characterised by expertise, responsibility and innovation
- A diverse workplace with regards to gender, age and cultural background
- Competitive terms of employment and excellent benefit schemes


**See the entire application and apply [here](https://statkraft.easycruit.com/vacancy/2482625/195327?iso=gb)**', '2020-03-04 14:51:59+00', '2020-03-22 22:55:55+00', false, '2020-03-22 22:55:55+00', 'https://statkraft.easycruit.com/vacancy/2482625/195327?iso=gb', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

