INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (632, NOW(), 103, 'Summer Internship 2022 – Information Technology And Digitalisation', 'As a summer intern at Equinor, you will be joining 20,000 colleagues delivering oil, gas, wind and solar power to 170 million people worldwide. By 2050, we aim to become a net-zero company and deliver the energy the world needs without to global ...', '### Job Description
As a summer intern at Equinor, you will be joining 20,000 colleagues delivering oil, gas, wind and solar power to 170 million people worldwide. By 2050, we aim to become a net-zero company and deliver the energy the world needs without contributing to global warming. It’s one of the defining challenges of our time and attracting and developing the brightest minds is critical to our success.

#### The position
The summer internship programme is aimed at students from the second year of their higher education onwards, from technical and non-technical backgrounds. To be eligible, you must be enrolled as a student between June and August of 2022 and have work eligibility for the country you are applying for.  
  
You will join us on a six-week hybrid programme - partly physical and partly virtual - designed to give you the experience and skills you need in your studies and future career. Working flexibly, you will split your time between working as part of a team within one of our business areas and delivering a group project with several of your fellow interns. In this period, you will have one-week off from the 18 July to the 22 July 2022.

By joining us, you will be part of a technology powerhouse where we have brought together research, technology, digitalisation, and IT with the aim to deliver safe and efficient technology, innovative solutions to problems and create new opportunities.

We utilize advanced technologies such as cloud computing, microservice architectures and machine learning to unlock the potential of the vast amounts of data we have.

Cyber security has a high focus in Equinor and is a critical function to safeguard our operations and enable our digital ambitions. The Cyber Defence Center in Equinor is responsible for detecting and responding to cyber threats in IT and IACS (Industrial Automation & Control Systems).  

Fields within discipline:  
-   Information Technology
-   Cloud computing
-   Software development
-   Data analytics, data science and Artificial Intelligence (AI)
-   Cyber security and risk management
-   Enterprise data management
-   Automation, robotics and remote control
-   Geomatics, Geodesy, Geographic Information Science

By joining our team in Information technology & Digitalisation you will have the opportunity to:
-   Work with new technology
-   Solve complex and challenging tasks
-   Learn from competent team members
-   Receive relevant training
-   Take part in social events

#### You
Some qualities are essential for Equinor. You identify with our values of being open, collaborative, courageous and caring, which guide our decisions and help us succeed and grow. You make safety your priority and contribute to our zero-harm culture. For this position, we are also looking for:
-   Bachelor, Master’s degree or PhD with a good academic record within STEM subjects
-   Fluent in English and preferably a second working language
-   No more than one year of relevant full-time work experience
-   Completed at least two years of higher education
-   Be enrolled as a student between June and August of 2022
-   The interns need to be located in the country where the internship takes place during its full duration
-   Candidates must have the necessary work permit for the country in which, and at the time, they are applying for a position. Please note that we do not facilitate work permits for this role. Read more about it in the national authorities’ pages: [Norway](https://www.udi.no/)
-   Extracurricular activities and/or voluntary work is an advantage

Your personal qualities:
-   Ability to live by our safety and security expectations
-   High ethical standards
-   Good communication skills
-   Global mindset
-   Team player with the ability to work and deliver results in a diverse environment
-   Have a positive attitude to take on new challenges and adapt to dynamic environments
  
Equinor is an equal opportunities employer, and we welcome applications from all candidates who meet the educational and experience requirements, including candidates with disabilities. If you have any specific requirements for any stage in our process, please make this clear in your application, and our team will be happy to support you.

#### General information

Please, make sure that you attach the documents below during the application. Note that applications submitted without these attachments will unfortunately not be evaluated:
-   CV/ resume in English
-   Cover letter
-   Transcripts of records (or other documents describing subjects and grades) obtained to this point during your studies in English or Scandinavian language. If you are in the process of completing a degree, please upload an official temporary transcript.

To ensure an efficient recruitment process, please be informed that you may apply for a maximum of three roles per country.

Candidates are expected to openly offer all relevant information about themselves during the recruitment process. All permanent and temporary hires will be screened against relevant sanctions lists to ensure compliance with sanctions law.

### Why join us?
The summer internship is an opportunity for you to get to know Equinor, our people and culture, and the way we work. You will work on various tasks and projects that will provide both value for you and Equinor.

**Hands-on experience.**
You will spend part of your internship working on tasks and projects within the discipline you have applied for, giving you first-hand experience of the strategy, processes and culture in your team. Your hiring manager will be your main point of contact and will be responsible for ensuring you get the most out of your time with us. You will also be allocated a buddy who will provide support and follow your experience in Equinor.  
  
**Multidiscipline project delivery.**
The remainder of your time will be spent working on a group project with other students from a variety of academic backgrounds. Supporting you on this project will be a subject matter expert who will act as a mentor and advisor to your task. Over the course of this project, you will develop key skills such as collaboration, leadership, communication, presentation skills and planning and time management.

**Learning and development.**
We will be delivering a series of learning sessions that provide an overview of our business and introduce you to some of the processes and methods we use at Equinor. These will include introductions to key areas of our strategy such as digitalisation, low carbon projects and our approach to safety and sustainability. You will also get to learn about our approach to project delivery and other methodologies that support our day-to-day deliveries.  
  
**Protecting your well-being.**
We are constantly developing our flexible working policy to meet the increasing demand for remote working, so you can be sure that your health and well-being will be a priority during your time with us. We also recognise that your summer internship is an opportunity to make connections that could last your entire career. That is why we will be introducing many opportunities to socialise with your fellow interns.

For more information visit Equinor''s website:  [https://www.equinor.com/](https://equinor.com/)', '2021-09-08 21:38:06+00', '2021-11-03 22:59:59+00', false, '2021-11-03 22:59:59+00', 'https://careers.peopleclick.eu.com/careerscp/client_statoil/external/gateway.do?functionName=viewFromLink&jobPostId=30930&localeCode=en-us', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (627, NOW(), 221, 'Internship i Folkeinvest – sommer/vinter 2022', 'Folkeinvest har opplevd en stor vekst det siste året, og vi ser frem til å ta dette videre inn i 2022. Som intern i Folkeinvest vil du få muligheten til å jobbe med utfordringer og muligheter tilknyttet den unge bransjen vi opererer i.', '### Om Folkeinvest

Folkeinvest er et verdipapirforetak som har spesialisert seg på folkefinansiering; vi gir alle muligheten til å delta i verdiskapingen - som gründer, investor eller heiagjeng. Vi legger til rette for at alle kan investere i det de tror på. Vår plattform folkeinvest.no er en effektiv møteplass mellom selskapene som søker kapital, og folk som ønsker å investere i morgendagens løsninger og spennende bedrifter.  
  
Vi ønsker å demokratisere aksjehandel og gi flere muligheten til å investere i gode oppstart- og vekstselskap. Norge er avhengig av et sunt næringsliv etter oljen, og det skal vi bygge sammen!  

### Internship i Folkeinvest sommer/vinter 2022

Folkeinvest har opplevd en stor vekst det siste året, og vi ser frem til å ta dette videre inn i 2022. Som intern i Folkeinvest vil du få muligheten til å jobbe med utfordringer og muligheter tilknyttet den unge bransjen vi opererer i.  
  
Som intern hos oss vil du lære mye – og målet er at vi skal lære minst like mye!  
Gjennom innspill fra interns med ulik kompetanse søker vi kunnskap og innsikt på en rekke områder og problemstillinger Folkeinvest står ovenfor. Du vil jobbe sammen med andre interns i et prosjekt, hvor blant annet analyse av videre ekspansjon, strategi og selskaper er sentrale stikkord. Prosjektet ledes av, og gjennomføres sammen med våre interns fra 2021; det blir med andre ord et ungt og energisk arbeidsmiljø. Parallelt med prosjektarbeidet er det muligheter for å bistå våre avdelinger; Marked, Kunde og Digital med dagligdagse arbeidsoppgaver avhengig av din kompetanse og interesse.  
  
Det er lenge til sommeren, og følgelig er det vanskelig å konkret utdype hva prosjektet og dine arbeidsoppgaver vil være, da vi hele tiden er i utvikling. Det oppstår nye problemstillinger og spørsmål vi ønsker svar på fortløpende, og du kan være trygg på at det du arbeider med neste sommer vil være av høy relevans for oss.  
  
Internshipet består av 1-2 introduksjonsuker i januar, og videre 6-8 uker på sommeren. Vi lover en morsom, spennende og lærerik sommer, hvor du får en unik innsikt i Norges største plattform for aksjebasert folkefinansiering. I Folkeinvest får man ansvar fra første dag; vi har troen på at det er sånn man lærer fort.  

## Vi søker deg som:

- «kjenner til JavaScript, git og agile prosesser»  
