INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (648, NOW(), 46, 'Software Engineering Summer Internship', 'We are looking for our new Software Engineering Summer Interns to join us Summer 2022.', '## Are you our new Software Engineering Intern?

Cisco Norway is a world leader in developing collaboration and video conferencing technology. We are 350 engineers who design all parts of our products - from idea to design, mechanics, audio, media processing and artificial intelligence. All this happens under the same roof in Lysaker at Cisco Webex Development Center. Our products are used by small businesses and large corporations, universities, governments and international organizations.


We are looking for our new Software Engineering Summer Interns to join us Summer 2022.


## What you will do:
During a summer here at Lysaker you will get the opportunity to explore a variety of technologies while working together with an existing team. It is important for us that our summer interns feel they are part of our team and that they get to work on real projects that are truly relevant and useful for us.



The project you will be working on will be decided based on your field of interest and on what we are currently working on. If you have a great idea, you might even get the opportunity to pursue this during your internship. These are some examples of projects that previous interns have been working on:


- real time multi head pose detection
- improving the microphone beam selector using deep learning
- office room analytics application based on live and historical sensor data from our devices
- noise reduction with deep learning
- synchronous camera focusing for immersive systems
- showing personal calendars in meeting rooms based on face recognition
- using falco on Kubernetes for threat detection in Webex

## Who you are:
More important than your track-record, are your commitment, curiousness and willingness to learn. We are looking for people who want to become an expert in their field trough working with us. In order to succeed, you also need to be a team player. We need to combine our brains, competences and expertise in order to deliver top of the shelf products.

In addition, do you:

- study towards a master’s or bachelor´s degree in a related subject?
- have some practical engineering experience with for example programming, testing, signal processing, network protocols or cloud technology?
- have a genuine interested in technology, willingness to learn?
- have the ability to live and work in Norway

## Why us? 
We are nothing without our people. We depend on our people’s creativity, curiosity and ability to work together to solve interesting problems in elegant ways, and we work hard to be a place where people thrive and grow.
We believe that happy people can make anything happen and are proud to be #1 World´s Best Workplace in both 2019 and 2020, and #1 Norway’s Best Workplace in 2021. We can offer you:

- a fun summer with a competitive salary, and real projects that are important for Cisco
- provide challenging and interesting tasks that are relevant to your education and creativity
- a Cisco Fun group – dedicated to creating great memories
- a Cisco Play group –that organizes yoga and weekly bootcamps in our in-house fitness center
- and of course, free ice cream on warm summer days!

Duration: 13. June – 14. August 2022 (8 weeks)

Application deadline: 31st October - we review applications on an ongoing basis


Upon applying please upload your cover letter, CV and university grade transcript.', '2021-09-16 06:00:00+00', '2021-10-31 22:59:59+00', false, '2021-10-31 22:59:00+00', 'https://jobs.cisco.com/jobs/IsAJob?projectId=1343429&source=Other+Job+Posting&tags=onlinentnu', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (969, NOW(), 267, 'Fullstack summer intern / part-time (Lysaker or Trondheim)', 'We''re looking for a student to join us as a fullstack engineer both part-time and for a summer internship in our mission to help businesses make better decisions using sensor data.', 'Disruptive Technologies (DT) is the award-winning developer of the world’s tiniest, zero-hassle wireless IoT sensors and cloud infrastructure. We bring together everything that’s required to build services and applications that collect data from wireless sensors. Our technology is used by startups, scale-ups, Fortune 500 companies, and everything in between to deliver solutions that range from replacing manual temperature measurements in hospitals to making buildings more efficient and easier to operate.

  

**We''re looking for a student to join us as a fullstack engineer both part-time and for a summer internship in our mission to help businesses make better decisions using sensor data. We design and create our own hardware, software, and application protocols to ensure we can provide the best experience possible. As a fullstack engineer you’ll be part of the cloud team, working on improving the user experience through customer facing applications and internal tooling that help our business thrive.**

  

**Some of the technologies we use**

-   For backend services, our primary programming language is [Go](https://go.dev/), but we occasionally also use [Python](https://www.python.org/).
-   We use [gRPC](https://grpc.io/) for all of our internal APIs, and define our asynchronous events in [Protocol Buffers](https://protobuf.dev/).
-   We track all of our infrastructure in code using [Terraform](https://www.terraform.io/).
-   Our cloud-provider is Google Cloud, where most of our workload runs on Google Kubernetes Engine. We prefer to use Cloud SQL with PostgreSQL for storing application state, and Cloud Pub/Sub as the message queue.
-   On the frontend side, we use React and Vue.js for internal-facing applications. Our customer-facing Studio application is currently written in AngularJS, and we’re planning a rewrite using either React or Vue.js.

  

**We’re looking for someone who**

-   Feels comfortable working in a modern development environment.
-   Have experience building, running, and debugging web applications using modern JS frameworks (Svelte, Vue, React, etc.).
-   Can put yourself in the shoes of your users and be a steward of crafting great experiences.
-   Is self-driven, caring, and can work in a team with other people.

-   Eye for design, product details, and polish is a strong plus.
-   Excited by new products and startups.

  

**You should include these in your application**

-   Your resume and/or LinkedIn profile.
-   A one-paragraph summary of your favorite project from any of your work, school or personal experiences.

  

**Location is at Lysaker and/or Trondheim.**

  

​If you feel like you don''t meet all of the requirements for this role, we encourage you to apply anyway. We know the confidence gap and imposter syndrome may get in the way of meeting incredible candidates, and we don''t want it to get in the way of meeting you.

  

Please submit your application within **31.3.2024** and we will get back to you shortly.

Read more at [www.disruptive-technologies.com](https://www.disruptive-technologies.com/)', '2024-03-11 09:26:00+00', '2024-03-31 21:59:00+00', false, '2024-03-31 21:59:00+00', 'https://disruptive.bamboohr.com/careers/61', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (649, NOW(), 46, 'Graduate Software Engineer', 'Are You Our New Graduate Software Engineer?', '## Are You Our New Graduate Software Engineer?


In Lysaker, near Oslo, you find Cisco Webex Development Center. We develop audio and video solutions that help millions of people connect and collaborate all over the world – without actually moving people around.

We make both hardware and software and develop all parts of Webex Devices under the same roof - from idea to design, mechanics, audio, media processing and artificial intelligence. Our products are used by small businesses and large corporations, universities, governments and international organizations – and even by Queen Elizabeth II.


We are now looking for a new Graduate Software Engineer.

## What You Will Do

Your role evolves as you get to know us, and we encourage you to try different roles and experience different teams and tasks. Our goal is making sure you can get the most of your potential, so that together we make the best possible products to help people connect and collaborate. When you arrive you get a mentor, so you always have someone to ask.



## In this role you will have the opportunity to:

- join different teams in search of your perfect spot.
- explore programming and contribute to our product development.
- apply all your creativity and knowledge to the quest to create great video conference solutions.
- be part of one of the largest specialist environments on video collaboration in the world.
- attend national and international courses, seminars, conferences and workshops in order to stay up to date and learn new skills.


## Who You Are

More important than your track-record, is your commitment, curiosity and willingness to learn. We are looking for people who want to become an expert in their field through working with us. In order to succeed, you also need to be a team player. We need to combine our brains, competences and expertise in order to deliver top of the shelf products.



## In addition, do you have

- a relevant bachelor’s or master’s degree, or adequate experience? Relevant degrees might be computer science, computer engineering, informatics, electrical engineering, or a related subject such as math or physics.
- an interest in programming and development?
- a willingness to learn new skills and broaden your knowledge?
- ambition, both on behalf of yourself and your product?
- the magic combination of creativity and thoroughness?

If this sounds like you, we are eager to hear from you!


## Why Us? 

We are nothing without our people. We depend on our people’s creativity, curiosity and ability to work together to solve interesting problems in elegant ways, and we work hard to be a place where people thrive and grow.


We believe that happy people can make anything happen and are proud to be #1 World´s Best Workplace in both 2019 and 2020, and #1 Norway’s Best Workplace in 2021. In addition to a competitive salary, insurance, and other benefits, we offer:


- a Cisco Fun group – dedicated to creating great memories
- a Cisco Play group –that organizes yoga and weekly bootcamps in our in-house fitness center – to strengthen your body and relieve your stress
- six weeks holiday – to make sure you’re well rested
- five (paid) days for volunteer work – to make the world a better place
- a day off on your birthday – because you deserve it
- and of course, free ice cream on warm summer days!


Start date: August 2022
Application deadline: 30th of January - we review applications on an ongoing basis

Upon applying please upload your cover letter, CV and university grade transcript.', '2021-09-16 14:33:55+00', '2022-01-30 22:59:59+00', false, '2022-01-30 22:59:59+00', 'https://jobs.cisco.com/jobs/IsAJob?projectId=1339425&source=Other+Job+Posting&tags=onlinentnu', '', 'FULLTIME', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (659, NOW(), 11, 'Sommerforskere – Digital Process Innovation 2022', 'SINTEFs visjon er "Teknologi for et bedre samfunn".  Sammen med våre oppdragsgivere utvikler vi kunnskap og løsninger som bidrar til økt, bærekraftig verdiskaping, eller som bidrar til bedre ressursutnyttelse og helt nye inntektsmuligheter.', 'SINTEFs visjon er "Teknologi for et bedre samfunn".  Sammen med våre oppdragsgivere utvikler vi kunnskap og løsninger som bidrar til økt, bærekraftig verdiskaping, eller som bidrar til bedre ressursutnyttelse og helt nye inntektsmuligheter.

