Har du spørsmål om denne stillingen? Ta kontakt med Harkamaljit Singh på harkamaljit.singh@spireconsulting.no eller +47 992 36 693', '2022-04-04 12:04:08+00', '2022-04-25 21:59:59+00', false, '2022-04-25 21:59:59+00', '', 'rekruttering@spireconsulting.no', 'PARTTIME', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (740, NOW(), 53, 'Blank søker nyutdannede teknologer for oppstart i 2023', 'Vi i Blank designer og utvikler digitale tjenester. Vi jobber med en kombinasjon av start-ups,
små og store virksomheter, og i tillegg utvikler vi egne produkter og tjenester når vi kommer
på noe bra – mest fordi vi synes det er gøy.', 'Planlagt oppstart: august 2023
Søknadsfrist: fortløpende

Blank er et ambisiøst og litt annerledes design- og teknologimiljø. Vi er et felleskap av
omtrent 50 svært dyktige designere og teknologer i et konsulentselskap hvor full åpenhet og
transparens er en selvfølge. Vi holder til i Torggata 15, rett ved Youngstorget.
Nå ønsker vi oss flere nyutdannede teknologer for oppstart i 2023.

# Dette vil du jobbe med
Vi i Blank designer og utvikler digitale tjenester. Vi jobber med en kombinasjon av start-ups,
små og store virksomheter, og i tillegg utvikler vi egne produkter og tjenester når vi kommer
på noe bra – mest fordi vi synes det er gøy. En av disse tjenestene er nå et eget firma med
14 ansatte 🎉 Du kan se noen eksempler på ting vi jobber med på bloggen, som Amoi, ice,
Karpe, Reisen til Spektrum (Sondre Justad), Morgenlevering og reMarkable. Tre år på rad er
også tjenester Blank har utviklet blitt nominert til Gulltaggen.

# Betingelser og slikt
- Hos oss får du gode betingelser – det er en selvfølge
- Vi praktiserer åpen lønn (helt på ordentlig)
- Du får være med å drive selskapet
- Du får være med å velge hvilke oppdrag du skal jobbe på
- Du blir del av et særdeles sterkt fagmiljø med veldig stor takhøyde
- Alle som begynner i Blank får aksjer og blir medeiere

# Faglig utvikling
Vi har blant annet satt av første fredag i måneden til innedag, en hel dag der du kan lære
deg nye ting eller bli enda bedre på ting du allerede kan. I tillegg til dette kan du selvfølgelig
dra på konferanser og kurs når du mener det er en god ide.

Søk jobb som teknolog i Blank
Les mer om oss på blank.no, sjekk ut bloggen vår eller ta kontakt med Kristine Berge på
kjb@blank.no om du vil vite mer.', '2022-05-22 13:46:00+00', '2022-09-23 13:45:42+00', false, NULL, 'https://www.blank.no/jobb-teknologi/', '', 'FULLTIME', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (737, NOW(), 254, 'Vi søker frontend-utvikler/fullstack-utvikler', 'Vil du være med på å skape fremtidens systemer? Vi søker frontend-utvikler/fullstack-utvikler! Perl, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, jQuery, XML, XSL m.m.', 'Extend AS er inne i en periode med sterk omsetningsvekst, vi har solide resultater og består av en fantastisk gjeng med ansatte!

For å videreutvikle programvaren og selskapet søker vi engasjerte og dyktige systemutviklere. Vi oppfordrer både deg med erfaring og deg som er nyutdannet til å søke!

Du vil bli en del av et raust og godt arbeidsmiljø, og vil jobbe mot spennende kunder innenfor helse, havbruk, industri, transport og offentlig sektor. Vi har store kunder som bl.a. Helse Midt-Norge, A-hus, de store apotekkjedene, Salmar, Oslo kommune, Fjord1 m.fl.

Ansatte i selskapet omtaler miljøet som veldig godt med en åpen tone og stor takhøyde. Systemutviklerene sitter samlet, og det er et godt samarbeidsklima med god sparring og fokus på utvikling. Stemningen er god og det er en kameratslig, trivelig og uformell gjeng som jobber sammen mot felles mål. Her får du muligheten til å påvirke og få eierskap.


### Hovedansvarsområder  
* Være med på å videreutvikle og forbedre programvare.
* Planlegge og videreutvikle ny funksjonalitet og nye moduler.
* Implementere ny funksjonalitet og forbedre eksisterende funksjonalitet.
* Delta i teknisk support til våre kunder.

### Ønskede kvalifikasjoner
* Gode programmeringsferdigheter og gjerne kjennskap til teknologiene vi bruker.
* Opptatt av programutvikling og ny teknologi.
* Løsningsorientert og glad i nye utfordringer.
* Mulighet til å velge plattform å jobbe fra (Linux, Microsoft etc)
* Utdanning tilsvarende Bachelor-eller Mastergrad innenfor informatikk/datateknikk.
* Beherske norsk flytende både muntlig og skriftlig.
* Rask til å sette deg inn i nye oppgaver og ny teknologi.
* Vi ønsker at du er kjent med eller har erfaring innenfor flere av følgende områder: Generell objekt orientert utvikling, Perl (benyttes om hovedspråk i applikasjonen), Web-teknologier som HTML, CSS, JavaScript, jQuery, XML, XSL m.m. Relasjonsdatabaser (MSSQL, PostgreSQL)

### Vi tilbyr
* En spennende stilling i et sterkt fagmiljø preget av åpenhet, samhold og trivsel.
* Konkurransedyktige betingelser og tilgang til en god bonusordning.
* Tilgang til kantine, medlemsskap i treningssenter, sykkelparkering og muligheter for parkering av bil.
* Flotte lokaler sentralt i Trondheim.
* Mange spennende og solide kunder.
* Veldig godt arbeidsmiljø og en god blanding av ansatte med hensyn til alder, kjønn og fagkompetanse.

Extend AS ble etablert i 1996 og leverer vårt egenutviklede, fleksible web baserte kvalitetssystem-og virksomhetsstyringssystem EQS til over 250 kunder og over 250.000 brukere. EQS er markedsleder i en rekke bransjer og leverer til en rekke spennende kunder, store og små, i privat og offentlig sektor. Selskapet er lokalisert på Leiv Erikson senter i Trondheim og har 12 ansatte som jobber med support, programvareutvikling, markedsføring, salg og rådgivningstjenester. Extend AS er eid av Confirma Software AB og representerer sammen med dem Norges største miljø for kvalitetssystemer og et stort Nordisk systemutviklingsmiljø.', '2022-05-12 11:33:23+00', '2022-06-12 21:59:59+00', false, '2022-06-12 21:59:59+00', 'https://www.finn.no/job/fulltime/ad.html?finnkode=257358450', '', 'FULLTIME', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (734, NOW(), 61, 'Security PhD fellowships available through Simula Research Laboratory', 'Simula Research Laboratory seeks applicants for three PhD positions offered as part of Simula’s work on security aspects of software engineering. These positions are located at Simula’s location in downtown Oslo, Norway.', 'Simula’s mission is to solve important and fundamental problems of science and engineering, with the main goal of benefiting and advancing society. We do this by concentrating on selected fields in ICT and performing excellent research, by developing our people, and by spinning out applicable results into profitable startups. Learn more about working at Simula on our careers page: https://www.simula.no/about/careers

Simula Research Laboratory seeks applicants for three PhD positions offered as part of Simula’s work on security aspects of software engineering. These positions are located at Simula’s location in downtown Oslo, Norway.

Each of the three positions is associated with a specific project and, while all the projects are at the intersection of security and software engineering, each project will require slightly different expertise and experience. Thus, Simula is seeking motivated and independent students from a wide range of training backgrounds, but particularly with a strong working knowledge in software engineering to take up these doctoral fellowships. Details regarding the specific projects and desired candidate profiles can be found on the project page (www.simula.no/available-projects), while more general information about what Simula can offer to the PhD fellows can be found here: https://www.simula.no/ecrs

An additional unique feature of this call is the opportunity for the PhD fellows to conduct a portion of their doctoral research at one of our major collaborative partners, such as Inria in France. As such, applicants should consider if they are prepared and eager to spend a portion of their fellowship (generally four to six months) as a visiting scholar at a partnering research organisation.

The duration of the doctoral fellowships can be 3 to 4 years, with at least 3 years of time dedicated to the doctoral work (courses, research, thesis) and up to 1 year for additional work. The purpose of this additional work is to contribute to researcher training and the development of transferable skills, and such duties can include teaching, contract research, supervision of masters students or interns, or the organization of meetings or conferences. The additional work is to be evenly distributed throughout the fellowship, and will be agreed upon together with the supervisor.

The time of initiation will vary depending on the project but can be as early as August 2022. All Simula-based PhD fellows will be enrolled in the doctoral program at one of our partnering degree-conferring universities, such as the University of Oslo or Oslo Metropolitan University.

As a PhD fellow at Simula you will work closely with your primary supervisors in Oslo, and undertake coursework and training related to computer science, software engineering and machine learning (the specific courses will depend on the particular student’s background and the needs of the project).

Teamwork is an important feature of the Simula working environment, and all PhD fellows will be expected to conduct themselves in an engaged and participatory way with their peers and colleagues at Simula. More about working at Simula is available here: www.simula.no/careers, and about the Simula Culture is available here: https://www.simula.no/about/simula-culture

## Candidate profiles: 

The scope of these projects allows students of many training backgrounds to be excellent candidates for these fellowships. However, because all the projects relate to software engineering in their nature it is strongly recommended that applicants have a working background in programming, security, software engineering and elements of data science including machine learning. Good knowledge of the scientific field addressed by the project(s) of interest is desirable. Strong quantitative and analytical skills are an advantage. **Beyond these general recommendations, the following requirements apply:**

1. Completion of Masters in an appropriate field for the project(s) of interest ahead of the PhD fellowship start date.
2. Suitable academic performance in Masters and undergraduate coursework relevant to the project(s) applied to (note that academic records are required).
3. Good communication and interpersonal skills (English is the working language). 

Note: For non-native English speakers, proof of competency with English is generally required for entrance to the doctoral program. Standardized test results or completion of a University degree in an English-speaking country is suitable.
Note: there may be additional requirements specific for the individual projects. These are published on the project pages, which can be found here: https://www.simula.no/available-projects.


## Simula offers:

- Excellent opportunities for performing high quality research, as part of a highly competent and motivated team of international researchers and engineers.
- An informal and inclusive international working environment.
- Generous support for travel and opportunities to build international networks, through conferences, established collaboration with industry, and exchange programs and research visits with other universities.
- Modern office facilities located in downtown Oslo, Norway.
- A competitive salary. Starting salary from NOK 491.200.
- Numerous benefits: access to company cabins, sponsored social events, generous equipment budgets (e.g., computer, phone and subscription), subsidized canteen meals, comprehensive travel/health insurance policy, etc.
- Relocation assistance: assistance with visas, complimentary Norwegian language courses, temporary accommodation, etc.
- Administrative research support: e.g., quality assurance process for grant proposals (including RCN and EU programs).
- Professional development and researcher training opportunities through the Simula Academy. 
- Flexibility in working conditions: our employees’ health and well-being is a priority and we encourage them to make use of our flexible work arrangements to help balance their work and home lives efficiently.
See our https://www.simula.no/careers

## Application requirements:

To apply for one of the doctoral fellowships hosted at Simula, candidates will need to select at least one of the projects from this call. Detailed project descriptions are provided here, and each applicant is permitted to select up to two projects to which they would like to apply. The application must include:

1. A cover letter summarising the candidate’s background and motivation, relevant experience and qualifications, and listing in ranked order the project(s) to which the candidate wishes to apply.
2. Curriculum vitae: educational background, any prior research experience and specific research project involvement, working experience (in particular, any relevant academic or industrial work), list of publications (e.g., scientific papers and publication of conference contributions)
3. Copies of transcripts and diplomas from Bachelor and Master’s degrees. If you have not yet have your Master''s diploma, please submit your transcripts for your graduate courses so far.
4. Letters of reference, and contact information (name, current position, relation to the candidate, phone and email) for up to three academic and research-oriented referees.

All of the above should be submitted via the provided form below – applications submitted by email will not be considered. 

Note: For non-native English speakers, proof of competency with English is generally required for entrance to the doctoral program. Standardized test results or completion of a University degree in an English-speaking country is suitable. 

## Deadline:
We are accepting applications for these positions until **1 May, 2022**.

For more information:

- For general questions regarding the recruitment process, please contact Stian Engen, Senior advisor (stianen@simula.no).
- For project-specific questions, please contact the main supervisor specified for the project:
 - Simula_project_1: Dr. Shaukat Ali, shaukat@simula.no
 - Simula_project_2: Dr. Dusica Marijan, dusica@simula.no
 - Simula_project_3: Dr. Helge Spieker, helge@simula.no
 
## About Simula and Norway

Simula is a publicly owned research laboratory that conducts research in Information and Communication Technology. Our research is focused in the fields of scientific computing, software engineering, communication systems, machine learning and cybersecurity.

Simula''s main objective is to solve fundamental problems of science and engineering that are of genuine value for society. This is achieved through high-quality research, education of graduate students, industry collaboration, and commercialization. Since 2001, scientific evaluations conducted by the Research Council of Norway has repeatedly placed Simula at the forefront of international research in ICT. In the most recent in-depth evaluation, the full range of research at Simula as given the grade of “excellent”.

Simula currently employs approximately 190 individuals from 35 countries and strives to create inclusive working environments. We strive to be an inclusive workplace.


*Simula Research Laboratory uses Semac´s background check in our recruitment process.*', '2022-04-07 10:28:19+00', '2022-05-01 21:59:59+00', false, '2022-05-01 21:59:59+00', 'https://www.simula.no/about/job/security-phd-fellowships-available-through-simula-research-laboratory', '', 'FULLTIME', false, false);

