INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (758, NOW(), 103, 'Graduate 2023 - Information Technology & Digitalisation', 'As a graduate at Equinor, you’ll be joining 20,000 colleagues delivering oil, gas, wind and solar power to 170 million people worldwide.', 'As a graduate at Equinor, you’ll be joining 20,000 colleagues delivering oil, gas, wind and solar power to 170 million people worldwide. By 2050, we aim to become a net-zero company and deliver the energy the world needs without contributing to global warming. It’s one of the defining challenges of our time and attracting and developing the brightest minds will be critical to our success.

The programme lasts for 2-years and includes rotations of 3-12 months across functions, business areas or locations. Head over to our [careers site](https://www.equinor.com/careers/graduates) for a more detailed overview of what you can expect if you join us.


### The position

Information Technology plays a vital role in accelerating the energy transition within Equinor and in shaping the future of energy. IT & Digitalisation is part of everything we do and a key enabler for value creation as well as secure and compliant operations.  
  
By joining us, you will be part of a technology powerhouse where we have brought together research, technology, digitalisation, and IT with the aim to deliver safe and efficient technology, innovative solutions to problems and create new opportunities.  
  
We utilize advanced technologies such as cloud computing, microservice architectures and machine learning to unlock the potential of the vast amounts of data we have.

By joining our team in Information Technology & Digitalisation you will have the opportunity to work within the following fields:  

-   Information Technology
-   Cloud computing
-   Software development
-   Data analytics, data science and Artificial Intelligence (AI)
-   Data Engineering
-   Enterprise data management and Data Architecture
-   Automation, robotics, and remote control
-   Geomatics, Geodesy, Geographic Information Science (GIS)


### You

Some qualities are essential for Equinor. You identify with our values, open, collaborative, courageous and caring, which guide our decisions and help us succeed and grow. You make safety your priority and contribute to our zero-harm culture. For this position, we are also looking for:  

-   Master’s degree or PhD with strong academic record within STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics) subjects.
-   No more than two years of relevant fulltime work experience.
-   Fluent in English and preferably a second working language.
-   Extracurricular activities and/or voluntary work is an advantage.

Every role and business area requires its own specific set of skills and personal attributes. Some of the qualities and attributes we look for include:

