INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (948, NOW(), 237, 'GPU Software Intern', 'Do you want to learn more about how we in Arm design our GPUs, CPUs, AI accelerators and other first-class IP that powers smartphones, self-driving cars, smart-watches, data-centers and just about any piece of electronics in the world?', '## **Job Overview:**

Search your pockets and pick up a device that most likely is flat, fits in your palm and has a shiny glass surface. With the help of this device, you can buy bus tickets, keep track of your work-out sessions, watch movies, play a game or record your next social media dance video post. For some reason, the world has settled calling them smart-devices, but the compute superpowers of the CPU, GPUs and AI accelerators in the device you are holding are so ludicrous that the result seems magic.

Do you want to learn more about how we in Arm design our GPUs, CPUs, AI accelerators and other first-class IP that powers smartphones, self-driving cars, smart-watches, data-centers and just about any piece of electronics in the world? Then you should consider joining the team in Trondheim, Norway.

In 2006 Arm acquired Falanx, a small Norwegian start-up developing Graphics Processing Units. The team now counts 200 employees from more than 30 different nationalities. We are based in Trondheim, the beautiful technological capitol of Norway. Here the team combines hiking, skiing, and trips on the fjord with developing Mali, the world''s most shipped GPU.

We work in a multi-site, multi-team and multi-cultural environment. If you are creative and passionate about new technologies we would love to hear from you!

## **Responsibilities:**

Being part of our software team, your assignments cover:

● Prototyping of ideas

● Investigations of application usage patterns

● Experimental driver feature implementations

## **Required Skills and Experience:**

In order to be considered, you will be studying Electronic Engineering, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or another relevant subject. Other degree types may be considered provided you have relevant skills.

## **“Nice To Have” Skills and Experience:**

● Linux knowledge

● C/C++ knowledge

● Python knowledge a plus

● Eager to experiment and work

● Possessing good intrinsic motivation

## **In Return:**

We offer internships where you will make a real impact, while also building on key skills for your future studies and employment.

Working on interesting new projects is exciting, but we also know how important it is to receive support. We make sure you have regular catch-ups with your line manager who will be able to offer ongoing support, feedback, and development opportunities. You will also be given a certain amount of flexibility and freedom in how you decide to complete your projects/tasks.

As well as being offered a competitive salary, there are also opportunities to get involved in some of the many social events that are organized within Arm.

ARM is also part of the summer internship program WorkationTRD in Trondheim, Norway. WorkationTRD offers an unique summer social program to all interns across the 25 participating tech companies. Activities include bouldering, Escape room, go-karting, beer tasting and much more, all at no cost to interns! This summer program is an excellent opportunity to make friends for life and meet interns from other tech companies in Trondheim. We at ARM and WorkationTRD will make sure you have an unforgettable summer in Trondheim.

## **#LI-NB1**

