Job candidates will not be obligated to disclose sealed or expunged records of conviction or arrest as part of the hiring process.
Accenture is committed to providing veteran employment opportunities to our service men and women.', '2023-03-16 13:37:53+00', '2023-04-09 21:59:59+00', false, '2023-04-09 21:59:59+00', 'https://accenture.wd3.myworkdayjobs.com/AccentureCareers/job/Lysaker/Summer-Internship-2023---Security_R00150256', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (874, NOW(), 290, 'Are you passionate for AI?', 'For our headquarters in Trondheim, we are looking for an ambitious and skilled candidate as a System Developer to strengthen the AI team in our Tolling Systems group.', 'Developer – Image Processing Systems

**For our headquarters in Trondheim, we are looking for an ambitious and skilled candidate as a System Developer to strengthen the AI team in our Tolling Systems group.**

Traffic is an important part of our daily life, yet the toll it takes on society is way too high. In Q-Free, we see how important it is to ensure sustainable mobility for current and future generations. Q-Free is an international company that innovates and delivers ITS (Intelligent Transportation Systems) solutions worldwide, and we are proud to have employees who are world-leading within their fields of competence.

As a member of the Tolling Systems group, you will be part of the team who is delivering efficient future solutions for Low Emission Zone enforcement and electronic Road User Charging. We build our high-performance and high-availability systems on a mixed set of technologies with both Q-Free and Third-Party products. Key activities are system development for high-performance and -availability, integrating with sensors, cameras and image processing methods.

The AI team within the Tolling Systems group develops neural networks for in image detection and classification of vehicles. Q-Free sees AI as an area that will have a large role in the future of our system development.

## Key responsibilities:

* Developing AI for different use cases.
* Developing neural networks for image detection and classification.
* Image processing systems.
* Realtime performance optimization.
* Integration with sensor systems.
* Industrial use of AI tools as machine learning and neural networks.

## Experience in any of the following areas is beneficial:

* Knowledge of statistical and algorithmic models.
* Working with large data sets and writing efficient code.
* Modern versions of Java, C/C++ and Python.

## We are searching for a person who:

* Has a genuine interest and good understanding of technology.
* Has familiarity with deep learning algorithms and use of AI/ML frameworks.
* Has good cooperation skills and seek solutions in cooperation with others.
* Is self-motivated with a will to work both independently and in a dynamic team.
* Has good oral and written skills in both English and a Scandinavian language. Other language skills can also be a plus.
* Has a higher technical education on Bachelor or Master level.

We are searching for both newly graduates and somebody with some years of experience. Working location is Trondheim, Norway, but you must be prepared to do some traveling abroad in periods.

We are offering a position in a company in growth, with a high level of competence, big ambitions and competitive terms. The position has strong developing possibilities for the right person, with good possibilities to work on both national and international projects.

In the department, you will join a highly experienced team, with employees that would be considered subject matter experts on tolling solutions globally alongside younger engineers that are aspiring to grow and learn. The working environment is informal and there is a strong pay-it-forward culture where there are always colleagues that are willing to assist in ensuring we meet our goals.

## Om arbeidsgiveren

Q-Free ASA (OSE: QFR) is a global innovator in intelligent transportation systems that improve traffic flow, road safety, and air quality. With an open, collaborative approach to tolling, traffic and active transportation management, Q-Free works with customers and partners on every continent to digitize infrastructure and overcome modern mobility challenges for the greater good of society.
Headquartered in Trondheim, Norway, Q-Free has annual revenues of approximately 1 billion NOK (120 million USD) and employs 400 transportation innovators, experts and enthusiasts. To learn more about how Q-Free is changing the movements of life, visit www.q-free.com.', '2023-04-20 21:59:59+00', '2023-05-16 21:59:59+00', false, '2023-05-16 21:59:59+00', 'https://www.finn.no/job/fulltime/ad.html?finnkode=296072734', '', 'FULLTIME', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (875, NOW(), 103, 'Graduate 2024 – ​​Information Technology', 'As a graduate at Equinor, you’ll be joining 21,000 colleagues delivering oil, gas, wind, and solar power to 170 million people worldwide', '**Equinor**

As a graduate at Equinor, you’ll be joining 21,000 colleagues delivering oil, gas, wind, and solar power to 170 million people worldwide. By 2050, we aim to become a net-zero company and deliver the energy the world needs without contributing to global warming. It’s one of the defining challenges of our time and attracting and developing the brightest minds will be critical to our success.  

The programme lasts for 2-years and includes rotations of 3-12 months across functions, business areas or locations.  


**The position:**

IT plays a crucial role in accelerating the energy transition, enabling value creation, and ensuring secure and compliant operations. Together, we shape the digital enterprise, secure the present, and enable the future.  

In Information Technology & Digitalisation, you''ll be tackling exciting and complex tasks, leveraging big data and cutting-edge technologies. We focus on building internal solutions that drive efficiency and enable digital transformation.  As part of our team, you''ll work alongside experienced professionals, collaborating to shape the future of energy. 


When joining our team in Information Technology & Digitalization you will have the opportunity to work within:

Information Technology.  
Cloud computing.
Software development.  
Data analytics, data science and Artificial Intelligence (AI).  
Data engineering.
Enterprise data management and Data Architecture.
Automation, robotics, and remote control .
Geomatics, Geodesy, Geographic Information Science (GIS).
Tasks may include:

Solve challenging tasks using the latest technologies.
Work with big data to drive insights and innovation.
Build internal solutions to enhance efficiency and effectiveness.
Utilize new technology to enable digital transformation.
Continuously learn and develop as part of a large (and growing!) internal IT community.


**You:**

Some qualities are essential for Equinor. You identify with our values, open, collaborative, courageous and caring, which guide our decisions and help us succeed and grow. You make safety your priority and contribute to our zero-harm culture. For this position, we are also looking for:

Master’s degree or PhD with good academic record within ​​STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics) subjects
Completed degree by the year of starting (2024). 
Fluent in English. 
No more than two years of relevant fulltime work experience. 
Formal experience is not a requirement.
Extracurricular activities and/or voluntary work is an advantage. 
Your personal qualities: 

Ability to live by our safety and security expectations. 
High ethical standards. 
Good communication skills. 
Global mindset.  
Team player with the ability to work and deliver results in a diverse environment.
Have a positive attitude to take on new challenges and adapt to dynamic environments.
Equinor is an equal opportunities employer and we welcome applications from all candidates who meet the educational and experience requirements, including candidates with disabilities. If you have any specific requirements for any stage in our process, then please make this clear in your application and our team will be happy to support you. 



**General information:**

 Please make sure that when applying, you attach the following: 

CV/ resume in English. 
Transcripts of records (or other documents describing subjects and grades) in English or Scandinavian language obtained to this point during your studies. If you are in the process of completing a degree, please upload an official temporary transcript.
Applications submitted without these attachments will unfortunately not be evaluated.  

To ensure an efficient recruitment process, please be informed that you may apply for a maximum of 3 Graduate roles per country. 

Candidates are expected to openly offer all relevant information about themselves during the recruitment process. All permanent and temporary hires will be screened against relevant sanctions lists to ensure compliance with sanctions law.

**Why join us?**

To succeed together, we all need to feel able to perform at our best.  That’s why we offer:  

Learning and development.  You’ll have access to on-the-job-training and mandatory physical and virtual learning modules, work rotations, networking opportunities and access to courses offered by our Equinor university. You’ll also get a buddy and a mentor to help you adapt and provide advice during the programme.   

Wellness and work-life balance. Our benefits packages are designed to help you balance work and life at all stages of your career, including health insurance and other benefits for your physical and mental wellbeing, a flexible working policy and a global parental leave policy. We also provide access to holiday cabins in Norway and selected other locations.   

An inclusive culture. An inclusive culture allows us to harness the unique experiences, knowledge, and backgrounds of our 21,000 employees. Ultimately, we believe we’ll be more creative, innovative, and resilient if everyone in Equinor feels safe in bringing their whole self and their ideas to work.   

Financial rewards. Equinor’s compensation package includes competitive cash compensation and an opportunity to join our share savings plan. In most of our locations we offer pension arrangements aiming to safeguard our employees after retirement.  

For more information visit Equinor’s website: https://www.equinor.com/careers/graduates', '2023-08-08 15:25:02+00', '2023-09-04 21:59:59+00', false, '2023-09-04 21:59:59+00', 'https://careers.peopleclick.eu.com/careerscp/client_statoil/external/en-us/jobDetails.do?functionName=getJobDetail&jobPostId=45946&localeCode=en-us', '', 'OTHER', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (873, NOW(), 290, 'Our complex systems need your experience with SW-development and architecture', 'We develop and deploy software running on Q-Free’s installations around the world. As Solutions Architect in our Tolling Systems group you will be responsible for a reusable baseline solution-architecture.', 'We develop and deploy software running on Q-Free’s installations around the world. As Solutions Architect in our Tolling Systems group you will be responsible for a reusable baseline solution-architecture, which also enables customization for specific customer deliveries.

You will be part of a strong team delivering efficient future solutions for Low Emission Zone enforcement and electronic Road User Charging. We build our high-performance and high-availability systems on a mixed set of technologies with both Q-Free and Third-Party products and work closely with our world-leading R&D department.

In Q-Free, the Solution Architects work cross-functionally in close collaboration with Solution Owners, Business Development and Development Project Management to ensure that the solution architecture meets business needs for our organization and the customer alike. In this role you also get to influence development processes by choosing the right technology and tools in order to reach Q-Free’s high expectations towards delivery, quality, and security.

## Key responsibilities as Solution Architect

* Design, development, and verification of baseline solution architecture
* Developing specifications for integration interfaces between internal subsystems, in collaboration with subsystem product owners
* Ownership of the overall architectural documentation e.g., descriptions, instructions, and policies, including content needed for sales and system delivery
* Provide support to the Tolling System sales teams globally through technical requirement- and risk analysis, identifying adaptations, and reviewing related content for tender/RFI responses.
* Supporting system engineers in the product- and system development process
* Market intelligence analysis with global and regional sales teams, and business development
* Compile, own and present solution architecture roadmap

## What are your key qualifications?

We believe you have a broad experience in solution architecture within IT/OT infrastructure and operations. Genuine interest and good understanding of technology is highly valued. You have great communication and cooperation skills, and enjoy seeking solutions in collaboration with both internal and external stakeholders.
We believe it is beneficial if you have formal education on Bachelor or Master level within IT, SW development or similar areas. You should have at least five years of experience, but we do encourage ambitious candidates with relevant background to apply.

Our working language is English and we require that you have strong oral and written skills in both English and a Scandinavian language. Other language skills (e.g., French, Spanish) are also valuable.

## It is beneficial if you have experience within some of the following areas

* Heterogeneous computing environments - Linux, Windows, RTOS
* DevSecOps or build automation
* Test automation
* Deployment, configuration, and operation of Active Directory, RabbitMQ,
* PostgreSQL, NetXMS, Puppet and ElasticSearch.
* Software development in Java (8 and later), C++, and scripting languages (Bash, Python, Perl)
* Complex systems where numerous software and hardware components work tightly together
*System delivery projects for external customers

## What’s in it for you?

We offer an opportunity in a growing company with a high level of competence, big ambitions and competitive terms. The position has strong developing possibilities for the right person, with good possibilities to work on both national and international projects.

In the department you will join a highly experienced team, with employees that would be considered subject matter experts on tolling solutions globally alongside younger engineers that are aspiring to grow and learn. The working environment is informal and there is a strong pay-it forward culture where there is always colleagues that are willing to help ensuring we meet our goals.

The working location is at Q-Free Headquarters in Trondheim, Norway. As we have projects all over the world some traveling will be expected.

## Om arbeidsgiveren

Q-Free is a leading global supplier of ITS - Intelligent Transportation Systems - solutions for efficient, safe, and environmentally friendly transportation. The company offers class-leading electronic tolling, parking, traffic management and Connected ITS (C-ITS)/Connected Vehicle systems. With approximately 350 employees, offices in 20 countries, and presence on all continents, Q-Free is a global company. Headquartered in Trondheim, Norway, Q-Free is listed on the Oslo Stock Exchange under the ticker QFR. Read more about Q-Free on our website: www.q-free.com', '2023-04-20 21:59:59+00', '2023-05-16 21:59:59+00', false, '2023-05-16 21:59:59+00', 'https://www.finn.no/job/fulltime/ad.html?finnkode=296985732', '', 'FULLTIME', true, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (872, NOW(), 289, 'Summer internship i Otto Mobility', 'Sommerjobb i Otto Mobility, ønsket klassetrinn: 3.klasse og oppover.', '*Vil du være med på å skape morgendagens mobilitetsløsninger? Folks reisevaner er i rask endring, og i stadig flere byer finner du nye mobilitetstjenester. Otto Mobility jobber med en rekke løsninger for bedrifter, kommuner og boligutviklere som vil tilby bildelingstjenester og få bedre oversikt over bilflåtene sine. For å få det til jobber vi i krysningspunktet mellom software og hardware. Vi tror at bil levert som en tjeneste bidrar til bærekraftig transport, gir folk frihet, og hjelper virksomheter med å spare penger. Vi er nå i en spennende fase hvor vi og ønsker å komme i kontakt med nysgjerrige studenter og nyutdannede som kan hjelpe og utfordre oss i dette arbeidet. Sammen kan vi bidra til å redusere antall biler på veiene.*

### Den perfekte kandidaten

Finnes nok ikke. Derfor oppfordrer vi alle til å søke, uansett hvor langt i studieløpet du er kommet så
ønsker vi å høre fra deg. Spesielt om du kan en eller flere ting i listen under:

- JavaScript/TypeScript
- React
- React Native
- Storybook
- NodeJS
- NestJS
- Mikrotjenester
- Terraform/IaaC
- Docker
- Kubernetes
- GCP, AWS eller Azure
- CI/CD Pipelines
- Git
- TDD

### Arbeidsoppgaver

Som intern vil du inngå i tech-teamet sammen med erfarne utviklere. Vi har en flat struktur og du vil
kunne aktivt påvirke valgene vi tar. Du må være selvgående og tørre å ta ansvar for eget arbeid.
Prosjektet for sommeren er tiltenkt å havne i vår produksjon. Med andre ord vil du her få jobbe med
reelle problemstillinger som skal komme våre kunder til gode. Dette kan være innenfor et bredt
spekter av områder, herunder:

- Ny funksjonalitet til vår mobilapp (React Native)
- Modellering av dataflyt (data fra bil, big data)
- Ny funksjonalitet til vårt flåtestyringsverktøy (React)
- Ny funksjonalitet i vår backend (NestJS)
- Forbedre våre CI/CD pipelines

### Hvem er Otto Mobility egentlig?

Otto utvikler blant annet bildelingsløsninger , og vi er et heleid datterselskap i Bertel O. Steen-konsernet. Selv om vi har en trygg eier i ryggen, styrer vi vår egen hverdag og operer som en start-up. Vi har kontorer sentralt i Oslo.

Bertel O. Steen er et av Norges største service- og handelsselskap og importerer bilmerkene Mercedes-Benz, smart®, Peugeot, Kia, Citroën, DS, Opel, Fiat, Fiat Professional, Jeep, Alfa Romeo, Fuso og Setra til Norge.

Vi i Otto liker å utfordre det tradisjonelle eierskapet til bil, og hver eneste dag kommer vi littnærmere fremtiden.', '2023-04-18 12:46:10+00', '2023-05-03 21:59:59+00', false, '2023-05-01 21:55:55+00', 'https://www.otto.no/sommer-intern-til-otto-mobility', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', true, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (876, NOW(), 291, 'Service Tekniker', 'Vi søker en Servicetekniker til vår Hardware avdeling, for deltidsstilling/tilkalling.', 'Vi søker en Servicetekniker til vår Hardware avdeling, for deltidsstilling/tilkalling. Utstyret i vår portefølje vil være nytt for de fleste, så opplæring vil bli gitt. Det viktigste er at du har interesse for elektronikk/tech. Stillingen kan passe fint for studenter som ønsker seg relevant arbeidserfaring ved siden av studiet, men andre søkere er også velkommen. Vi har fleksibel arbeidstidsordning og oppgavene kan utføres både dagtid, ettermiddag og kveld. Opplæring legges til dagtid etter avtale.

Stillingen er en midlertidig stilling med varighet ut året. Estimert 20-40% stilling, gjerne mer ved behov/ønske etter avtale med nærmeste leder. Stillingen lønnes med 205kr pr time.

Årsaken til at dette er en midlertidig stilling er fordi vi forventer endringer i behovet for servicetimer det neste året, knyttet til pågående og evt. nye prosjekter. Det er mulighet for forlengelse dersom behovet for servicetimer fortsatt er tilstede.

### Hva kan vi tilby:
* Flotte kontorlokaler på Falkenborg (ved Sirkus shopping)
* Godt arbeidsmiljø med lønningstreff hver måned, sosiale tilstelninger på kontoret og Trondheims kanskje beste lunsj
* Spennende og internasjonalt miljø – våre team er satt sammen på tvers av landegrenser
* Gode pensjon- og forsikringsordninger
* Fleksibel arbeidstid


### Arbeidsoppgaver:
* Klargjøring av HW-/SW-leveranser til kunder
* Rapportere fremdrift og avvik
* Feilsøking og reparasjon av hardware
* Andre oppgaver som faller naturlig inn under rollen, og evt. ekstra oppgaver ifm. ferieavvikling ol. på teamet.
 

### Vi leter etter noen som er/har:
* Kjennskap til bruk av Microsoft Office 365
* Teknisk innsikt og interesse
* Liker både varierte oppgaver og rutinearbeid
* Du har gode samarbeidsevner på tvers av avdelinger og er løsningsorienter
* Ansvarsfull - levere det du skal i tide og kan jobbe selvstendig
* Nøyaktig og strukturert
* Behersker norsk og engelsk skriftlig og muntlig

**Nice to have**: Kjennskap til Android og Linux er en fordel som vil hjelpe deg med oppgaver knyttet til feilsøking på vår hardware portefolio, men er ikke et krav.

### Rekrutteringsprosessen:
1. Søknader vurderes fortløpende og du kan bli kontaktet av HR for en kort telefonsamtale
