INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (895, NOW(), 273, 'Kickstart karrieren som konsulent i twoday', 'I twoday kan du starte karrieren som fast ansatt sammen med en håndplukket gjeng.
Målet er å få deg raskt ut på prosjekt – parallelt med spennede kurs, fagkvelder, reiser
og mye sosialt.', 'I twoday kan du starte karrieren som fast ansatt sammen med en håndplukket gjeng.
Målet er å få deg raskt ut på prosjekt – parallelt med spennede kurs, fagkvelder, reiser
og mye sosialt. Gjennom vårt skreddersydde opplæringsprogram og veiledning fra våre
erfarne konsulenter, leverer våre traineer raskt på toppnivå og skaper konkrete resultater
for kunder.

**En spennende start på arbeidslivet**

Nytt Krutt perioden kickstartes med kurs og opplæring innen relevante teknologier. I
løpet av det første året får du også reise på tur til flere av våre kontorer for å møte alle
twodays graduates, og få spennende faglig påfyll. I fjor gikk turene til Stockholm, Oslo
og København.

**Gjør en forskjell i sentrale norske virksomheter**

Som konsulent får du et unikt innblikk i ulike bransjer og lærer mange forskjellige
teknologier. Du har muligheten til å påvirke egen hverdag, og får en bratt læringskurve
og mange utfordringer. Vår ambisjon er å skape stolte øyeblikk, så hos oss vil du møte
engasjerte kolleger som alltid tar ansvar og strekker seg litt lenger for å levere over
forventning.

**twoday handler om mennesker**

Vi er opptatte av å skape et godt samhold mellom våre nyansatte. Du vil også raskt bli
godt kjent med erfarne kollegaer gjennom et bredt utvalg av sosiale og faglige
aktiviteter.

Å være markedsledende på engasjement og å ha en kultur hvor du blir sett, hørt og
satset på, ligger i ryggmargen til twoday. Det er ikke uten grunn at “hjerte” er en av våre
verdier. Hos oss bygger vi hverandre opp og heier på hverandre. Lagånd står sterkt hos
oss, og vi jobber derfor i team hvor du alltid har en god kollega å ta en kaffekopp med
eller spørre om råd.

Vi behandler søknader fortløpende. Alt du trenger å gjøre for å søke er å laste opp CV og
karakterutskrift, søknadsbrev er valgfritt. Benytt gjerne integrasjonen med Vitnemålsportalen
for karakterutskriften din.

Ønsker du å høre mer om stillingen eller har du spørsmål så er det bare å ta kontakt med
Åsne Stige på asne.stige@twoday.com', '2023-08-24 09:40:36+00', '2024-01-24 12:37:17+00', false, NULL, 'https://www.twoday.no/jobb-hos-oss/nytt-krutt', '', 'OTHER', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (997, NOW(), 323, 'Graduate 2025 Digital', 'We have big plans – do you want to be part of them?', 'Aker BP aims to become the leading oil and gas company by exploring and producing natural resources with low emissions and costs. Together with other Aker companies, we play and important role in the energy transition. Our future includes further growth and a desire to improve the industry.

We value diversity and everyone who works in Aker BP shall feel involved, included, and respected. We want everyone to thrive at work and develop in their roles, and are looking for you, who want to be part of our ONETEAM-culture.

We have big plans – do you want to be part of them?

As a graduate in Digital, you will be part of an inclusive and enthusiastic team, responsible for leading the way in the race to become the first data driven E&P company. You will be part of our Digital Transformation, which is imperative to reach this business goal. We are currently applying modern technologies such as digital twins, AI, machine learning, robotics, and automation, and we want your knowledge and inputs.

**Typical work tasks can be:**

- Being a part of digital transformation and process change in Aker BP: helping the business rethink old operating models, experiment more, and act in a more agile way in response to customers and competitors.
- Collaborating with alliances and internal business domains in developing data driven solutions including digital twin.
- Developing Aker BP''s modern and high-performance cloud data platforms and contributing to building a robust fundament for Cyber Security, Data Science, Data Engineering and Analytics.
- Playing an active role in optimizing data delivery through implementing new, and improving existing, data pipelines and integrations.

**Qualifications:**

- You have recently graduated or will graduate in 2025 with a master''s degree within a relevant discipline, e.g. Computer Science, Data Science, Mathematics, Robotics, Cybernetics, Automation, Cyber Security or similar.
- You have maximum two years of relevant professional experience.
- Interested in, and knowledge about, technology, automation, processes, information management and change management.
- English and/or Norwegian language working proficiency.

**We think you will thrive in Aker BP if this resonates with you:**

- Our SAFER values are the foundation for everything we do. Working with us means identifying with being Seekers, Accountable, Foreseeable, Engaged and Respectful.
- Cooperation is the very core of Aker BP. Working with us means wanting to be part of our ONETEAM-culture.
- At Aker BP, we put safety first. When working with us, we expect you to do the same.
- You like to work in teams and are a good communicator.
- You have a passion for digitalization and new digital tools.
- You have an interest in how data can be made available, interpreted, visualized, and used as a basis for various recommendations and decisions.

**Our commitment to you:**

- We are convinced diversity is an important element for success, and everyone in Aker BP should feel involved, included, and respected.
- We want you to develop. That''s why we are committed to providing you with varied experience and enhancing your expertise so you can build a CV for the future!
- We will offer you a competitive compensation package including a share savings program, and a solid pension scheme.
- We know that your health and a work-life balance are key factors for job satisfaction. That''s why we have good cafeterias, work-out facilities, and flexibility – in working hours.
- If something should happen to you, we will make sure you get help from the company health service and our insurance programs.
- Our offices have a universal design – accessible for all.

**What does it mean to be a graduate in Aker BP:**

- You will work closely with experienced professionals and gain experience and skills.
- You will develop through on-the-job training, seminars and graduate gatherings, courses, e-learning, and individual follow-up.
- You will learn about the industry and how we work in Aker BP.
- You will get a unique opportunity to build your network with current and recent graduates, our Young Professionals network, mentors and leaders across departments and disciplines.

**Location(s):** Stavanger or Oslo. Please specify your preferred location in your application.

**Please send us a little bit about yourself, your CV and your transcript by 15.09.2024.**

Please note that candidates will be evaluated continuously.

If you are currently enrolled in a master''s program, you can send a preliminary grade transcript.

Please note that applications without a diploma/preliminary transcript(s) will not be evaluated.

Background check and affiliation assessment in the recruitment process:

Background checks will be performed, following consent from relevant candidates. We ask that you enclose your diploma/grade transcript with your application.

An assessment of affiliation to high-risk countries is carried out as part of the recruitment process for all positions in Aker BP:

- All applicants will be asked to answer three questions as an initial screening of affiliations to high-risk countries*.
- If the answer to any of these questions is YES, an additional questionnaire will be sent to candidates who disclose affiliation AND are selected to proceed in the process.

The affiliation assessment is solely based on non-discriminatory categories of information and does not involve direct differential treatment due to the candidate''s ethnicity or other protected characteristics. The assessment of affiliation to high-risk countries is not an assessment of the candidate''s ethnicity or national origin, but an assessment of how closely the candidate is tied to the country through factors such as citizenship, family relations, financial assets, or other connections. Candidates with such connections may pose a potential security risk to Aker BP because such candidates may be more vulnerable to exploitation or recruitment by foreign threat actors.

- The definition of high-risk countries is based on Norwegian security authorities'' identification through their annual threat assessment and AkerBP security risk assessment. To address and mitigate this risk for the company and personnel, we wish to map candidates ́ affiliation to high-risk countries

**Contact information:** Anne Solhaug – anne.solhaug@akerbp.com', '2024-09-02 13:23:00+00', '2024-09-15 21:59:00+00', false, '2024-09-15 21:59:00+00', 'https://akerbp.com/available-positions/graduate-2025-digital/', '', 'OTHER', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (943, NOW(), 201, 'Join Volue Summer Internship Adventure', 'Are you ready to join one of Europe’s most exciting green tech companies and develop technology for a sustainable tomorrow? We''re on the lookout for the brightest and most tech-savvy minds to join our Volue family as Summer Interns!', '## About Us:

Our mission is to provide innovative services critical to society, unlocking a cleaner, better, and more profitable future. Working towards this goal, Volue has become a leading technology supplier and enabler of the green transition.

We''re all about turning ideas into reality, and our interns play a crucial role in making it happen. Our company culture is all about collaboration, continuous learning, and having fun while doing it. Here, you''ll have the opportunity to work on projects that truly matter and gain hands-on experience that can launch your career to new heights.

## What You''ll Do:

We ensure that summer students work in smaller groups in a working environment that is informal, fun, international, and rich in knowledge. Each group develops ideas for an existing product, further development, or creates new products. Brainstorming takes place in groups and close dialogue with specialists at Volue and our customers. We are working closely with our customers to create solutions, insights, and services that are suited to their needs. The students will have the same opportunity.

## You will:

- Work on exciting, real projects that challenge your skills and ignite your creativity.
- Collaborate with some of the industry''s brightest specialists, learning from the best in the field.
- Gain exposure to technologies we use to realise the green transition and industry trends.
- Bring your ideas to the table and see them come to life.
- Be a part of a supportive, inclusive, and fun-loving Volue Team!

## What We''re Looking For:

We are looking for students at various levels of study to join various Volue Teams!

### TEAM INSIGHT

If you have a background and interest in software engineering, data science, and market analysis – this is your team! You’ll work on projects with the ultimate goal of providing our customers with the best possible insights into the energy market. You will gain valuable experience working on real-world projects with a team of talented and experienced data scientists, market analysts, and software engineers. You can expect to work in teams, use Python, and follow an agile workflow with standups, code reviews, etc.

### TEAM DIGITAL WATER

If you have a background and interest in this combination: software engineering + data science + water – this is your team for the summer 2024! You’ll work on projects where the ultimate goal is to provide our customers with the best possible insights into the water industry and how digitalisation of processes can facilitate the green transition and assist water professionals in making resource-efficient and data driven choices. You will gain valuable experience working on real-world projects with a team of talented and experienced data scientists, software engineers and our water experts. You can expect to work in teams and the tasks will be tailored to relevant candidates.

### TEAM POWER GRID, DEVELOPMENT

If you have a background and interest in software engineering, workflow automation andsmart usage of the power grid – this is your team! You’ll work on projects where the ultimate goal is to provide our customers with the best possible experience on their journey towards renewable and stable power. You will gain valuable experience working on real-world projects with a team of motivated and experienced software engineer, software architects and power grid domain experts. You can expect to work in teams, do real coding on high valuable projects, follow an agile process and learn best practices work flow for creating high quality software, etc.”

### TEAM POWER GRID, CONSULTANCY

If you have a background and interest in technology, renewable energy, electrical power distribution, or geography/GIS, combined with knowledge in scripting/programming (e.g. Python), then Team Power Grid would be the team for you! You will gain valuable experience working on real-world projects with a team of talented and experienced consultants. The projects will aim to improve our services and deliveries to critical infrastructure for electrical grid companies in Norway and rest of Scandinavia.

### TEAM ENERGY SOLUTIONS

If you have a background and interest in energy and technology and background from  energy/power engineering or mathematical engineering,  combined with IT Completence then Team Energy Solutions is for you! You will be a part of our team delivering a comprehensive suite of decision support tools for power production planning, optimization and trading to energy companies.

Our summer program lasts for nine weeks, during which time there is a 3-week holiday. The program starts in the middle of June and ends in August.

The workplace for these internships will be in one of Volue''s office locations: in Trondheim, Arendal, or Oslo.

What we offer:

- Competitive compensation for your hard work.
- Opportunity to work on projects that impact the world.
- A positive, international working environment characterized by expertise, innovation and the urge to succeed
- Great colleagues in one of Europe’s most exciting green tech companies
- Possibilities for permanent employment upon internship completion

Final application date: 19th of November, 2023

We will consider applicants on an ongoing basis and we look forward to receiving your application!

### Volue and Workation program in Trondheim

If you will be joining our Program in Trondheim, you will also be a part of summerjob-project Workation which offers a unique summer program. Usually the program includes lots of activities – Høyt & Lavt klatrepark, Escape Room, beer tasting in ØX, free of charge for its participants. This program is a great opportunity to expand your professional network and make new friends!', '2023-10-24 14:01:52+00', '2023-11-19 22:59:59+00', false, '2023-11-19 22:59:59+00', 'https://volue.teamtailor.com/en-GB/jobs/3282648-volue-internship-2024?utm_campaign=jobs-widget&utm_content=jobs&utm_medium=web&utm_source=volue.teamtailor.com', '', 'SUMMER_INTERNSHIP', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (903, NOW(), 13, 'Deltid Trondheim', 'Har du lyst til å bli en del av et fagmiljø som elsker å lage gode digitale løsninger, setter kreativitet høyt og mener at flere hoder alltid er bedre enn ett?', '**Vi er på utkikk etter flere deltidsansatte til vårt kontor i Trondheim!**

**Studerer du informatikk og ønsker å utvikle deg faglig gjennom praktisk erfaring? Vil du være en del av et tverrfaglig team som jobber med alt fra applikasjonsutvikling til innsikt og analyse? Er du interessert i teknologi og synes det virker spennende å bruke fagkompetansen din i IT-bransjen?**

Computas skal nemlig forsterke vår nyeste enhet med enda flere hyggelige smartinger. Vi ser nå etter nettopp deg som ønsker å utgjøre en forskjell i hverdagen og har lyst til å være med på å bygge og forme Computas Trondheim som nå består av 10 dedikerte ansatte.

Med 35 års erfaring har Computas opparbeidet seg en solid posisjon i markedet. Derfor vinner vi stadig nye oppdrag i offentlig og privat sektor, hvor vi jobber med samfunnsviktige løsninger og teknologi som gir mening. Men vi liker å se på oss selv som en utfordrer som hjelper våre kunder med å forbedre, forenkle og begeistre!

Vi søker nå en deltidsressurs med høyt faglig engasjement. Stillingen vil utgjøre ca 20% av en full stilling. Arbeidstidene vil variere etter behov og være fleksible for tilrettelegging tilpasset studiehverdagen, eksamensperioder o.l. Vi er opptatt av å finne en student med en profil som matcher vårt team og våre arbeidsoppgaver. Vi har et bredt ansvarsområde, og stillingens spesifikke innhold vil kunne tilpasses den rette kandidatens stryker.

**Vi ser etter deg som ønsker:**

- Relevant erfaring på siden av studiene
- Jobbe med ny og spennende teknologi i samfunnsnyttige prosjekt?
- Komme inn i et sterkt fagmiljø med en unik delingskultur
- Jobbe i tverrfaglige team med andre studenter og fast ansatte


Send oss en CV og et motivasjonsbrev der du forteller litt om hvorfor du er den rette kandidaten til stillingen. Fremhev gjerne det du allerede måtte ha av praktisk erfaring.', '2023-09-03 11:57:41+00', '2023-10-01 21:59:59+00', false, '2023-10-01 21:59:59+00', 'https://careersno.computas.com/jobs/3106451-deltid-trondheim', '', 'PARTTIME', false, false);

INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (902, NOW(), 13, 'Sommerjobb', 'Har du lyst til å bli med på vårt sommerjobb-program hvor du får prøve deg på hverdagen som konsulent?', 'Vi i Computas ønsker å gi deg som studerer teknologiske fag eller design, og går i 2., 3. eller 4. klasse muligheten til å bli med på vårt sommerjobb-program for å prøve deg på hverdagen som konsulent sommeren 2024.

Computas er en annerledes arbeidsplass med nesten 300 ansatte, og vi er 100% eid av våre ansatte. Skaperglede og samarbeid er kjerneverdier i vår måte å jobbe på. Vi jobber med noen av verdens mest spennende teknologier og drives av ønsket om å skape teknologisk innovasjon som gir menneskelig fremskritt.

**Her er tre ting vi er litt ekstra stolte av: **
- 100 % ansatteid
- Stort fokus på samarbeid og kunnskapsdeling
- Kontorer med takterrasse midt i Oslo sentrum

**Hvem er du?**
