-   You are currently studying at a university
-   You are self-driven, caring, and can work in a team with other people.

  

**What we can offer**

-   "Wow” factor technology and solutions and a wide scope in relation to services
-   A great company with award-winning products and the World as our market
-   A truly diverse environment with colleagues from different nationalities

-   Competitive pay and benefits, including pension and insurance
-   Top-notch location at Lysaker/ in Trondheim, close to public transportation

-   Opportunity to work from home when needed
-   Fun and development opportunities - regular social events and monthly hack-days
-   Working with the best of the best makes Disruptive Technologies an excellent place for learning and development, also outside your area of specialization.

  

**Apply today!**

Please submit your CV and include a short cover letter before October 1st.  
We would like you to center the cover letter around a technical project you have been a part of and which you feel passionate about. It could be a school project you enjoyed, your work in a student organisation or a private project you did on your own time. We are not looking to judge your results, but rather to learn more about your interests and how you like to work. We look forward to reading your application and we will get back to you shortly.  

