INSERT INTO job_listing (id, "createdAt", "companyId", title, ingress, description, start, "end", featured, deadline, "applicationLink", "applicationEmail", employment, "deadlineAsap", hidden) VALUES (962, NOW(), 310, 'Part-time Chief Technology Officer', 'Tribe is a platform designed to bring together like-minded individuals through shared hobbies and interests within a group setting.', '**Application Deadline:** 16 February 2023    
**Type:** Part-time   
**Location:** Hybrid / Gründerbrakka (NTNU)   
**Contact:** Send a short motivational letter (half page) and your CV to denny@tribeapp.info until the 16th of February 2024. Feel free to get in touch via e-mail or 46570570 (Denny) if you have any questions.   


**In search of a Chief Technology Officer**           
We are looking for a motivated individual that wants to grow into the role as CTO and join our team on a part-time basis. The CTO will play a crucial role in leading the technical development of our innovative platform, with a primary focus on developing and optimizing our iOS/Android app using React Native with Firebase integration.

**About Tribe:**           
Tribe is a platform designed to bring together like-minded individuals through shared hobbies and interests within a group setting. The Tribe app has been launched on both the Apple Store and Google Play, and we are currently in a testing phase to further develop the app based on the feedback we are getting.

**What Tribe offers:**           
We offer an opportunity for professional and personal growth, in a part-time position (remote work possible) at our office, Gründerbrakka, at NTNU, where you can immerse yourself in Norway''s entrepreneurial ecosystem. You are also entitled to participate in free events that Tribe arranges. Equity ownership for the right candidate can be discussed.

**Your tasks & responsibilities:**         
- Lead the technical vision and strategy, ensuring alignment with the overall goals of the company.
- Hands-on development using React Native to build a robust and user-friendly iOS/Android app.
- Integrate Firebase for real-time data synchronization, authentication, and other relevant features.
- Oversee the entire software development lifecycle, from ideation to deployment and maintenance.

**Who are we looking for?** 
- Experienced in React Native for cross-platform app development.
- Proficiency in Firebase for backend services, authentication, and real-time database management.
- Knowledge of the entire mobile app development process, including design, development, testing, deployment, and maintenance.
- Good problem-solving and analytical skills.
- Effective communication and interpersonal abilities, with the capacity to convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
- Experience as CTO or in a similar leadership role preferably in a startup environment is beneficial.
- Implement and enforce best practices in coding, testing, and documentation.
- Conduct regular code reviews to ensure high-quality, scalable, and maintainable code.

**Requirements:** 
- Experienced with app development projects, preferably with apps available on major app stores such as the Apple store or GooglePlay.
- Availability to work part-time
- min. 2nd year of your study       



Thank you for your interest in Tribe!', '2024-01-19 11:23:00+00', '2024-02-16 22:59:00+00', false, '2024-02-16 22:59:00+00', '', 'denny@tribeapp.info', 'PARTTIME', false, false);

